Dialogue: 0,0:00:29.71,0:00:31.39,Default,,0,0,0,,I'm Chelsea Pugh and I'm an
Dialogue: 0,0:00:31.39,0:00:33.01,Default,,0,0,0,,engineer on the Safari team.
Dialogue: 0,0:00:33.65,0:00:36.02,Default,,0,0,0,,Welcome to session 225, What's
Dialogue: 0,0:00:36.02,0:00:37.67,Default,,0,0,0,,New in Safari View Controller.
Dialogue: 0,0:00:38.86,0:00:40.17,Default,,0,0,0,,Safari View Controller has a
Dialogue: 0,0:00:40.17,0:00:42.33,Default,,0,0,0,,bunch of improvements on iOS 11.
Dialogue: 0,0:00:43.40,0:00:45.68,Default,,0,0,0,,It also has new APIs that were
Dialogue: 0,0:00:45.68,0:00:47.58,Default,,0,0,0,,inspired by feedback that we got
Dialogue: 0,0:00:47.58,0:00:48.30,Default,,0,0,0,,from developers.
Dialogue: 0,0:00:49.48,0:00:51.18,Default,,0,0,0,,I'm really excited to share some
Dialogue: 0,0:00:51.18,0:00:52.62,Default,,0,0,0,,of Safari View Controller's new
Dialogue: 0,0:00:52.62,0:00:56.70,Default,,0,0,0,,abilities with you today.
Dialogue: 0,0:00:57.61,0:00:59.66,Default,,0,0,0,,One main use case of displaying
Dialogue: 0,0:00:59.66,0:01:02.07,Default,,0,0,0,,web content on iOS is to allow
Dialogue: 0,0:01:02.07,0:01:04.44,Default,,0,0,0,,users to browse the web in your
Dialogue: 0,0:01:05.83,0:01:05.91,Default,,0,0,0,,app.
Dialogue: 0,0:01:05.91,0:01:07.72,Default,,0,0,0,,You might be displaying a list
Dialogue: 0,0:01:07.72,0:01:08.98,Default,,0,0,0,,of links that could lead the
Dialogue: 0,0:01:08.98,0:01:11.83,Default,,0,0,0,,user to news articles or maybe
Dialogue: 0,0:01:11.83,0:01:13.91,Default,,0,0,0,,your displaying a list of links
Dialogue: 0,0:01:13.91,0:01:15.54,Default,,0,0,0,,that could lead to information
Dialogue: 0,0:01:15.54,0:01:17.28,Default,,0,0,0,,of different topics on the web.
Dialogue: 0,0:01:18.32,0:01:20.55,Default,,0,0,0,,It could, these links could your
Dialogue: 0,0:01:20.55,0:01:22.27,Default,,0,0,0,,user anywhere on the web, and
Dialogue: 0,0:01:22.49,0:01:23.93,Default,,0,0,0,,you don't expect to know where
Dialogue: 0,0:01:23.93,0:01:25.22,Default,,0,0,0,,they'll end up ahead of time.
Dialogue: 0,0:01:26.09,0:01:27.37,Default,,0,0,0,,How many of you are doing
Dialogue: 0,0:01:27.37,0:01:30.37,Default,,0,0,0,,something like this in your app?
Dialogue: 0,0:01:30.48,0:01:31.49,Default,,0,0,0,,All right, there's a few of you
Dialogue: 0,0:01:31.49,0:01:32.03,Default,,0,0,0,,out there.
Dialogue: 0,0:01:32.45,0:01:33.28,Default,,0,0,0,,You're in the right place.
Dialogue: 0,0:01:35.19,0:01:37.17,Default,,0,0,0,,Another main reason that you'd
Dialogue: 0,0:01:37.17,0:01:38.72,Default,,0,0,0,,want to display web content on
Dialogue: 0,0:01:38.89,0:01:41.21,Default,,0,0,0,,iOS is to allow your users to
Dialogue: 0,0:01:41.21,0:01:42.48,Default,,0,0,0,,get authenticated with a
Dialogue: 0,0:01:42.55,0:01:44.26,Default,,0,0,0,,third-party service so that it's
Dialogue: 0,0:01:44.26,0:01:45.87,Default,,0,0,0,,data can be used in your app.
Dialogue: 0,0:01:46.55,0:01:47.64,Default,,0,0,0,,How many of you do something
Dialogue: 0,0:01:47.64,0:01:48.46,Default,,0,0,0,,like that in your app?
Dialogue: 0,0:01:50.01,0:01:51.20,Default,,0,0,0,,You're also in the right place.
Dialogue: 0,0:01:53.28,0:01:54.92,Default,,0,0,0,,And for those of you that are
Dialogue: 0,0:01:54.97,0:01:56.45,Default,,0,0,0,,providing those experiences to
Dialogue: 0,0:01:56.45,0:01:57.93,Default,,0,0,0,,your user, how many of you are
Dialogue: 0,0:01:57.93,0:01:59.44,Default,,0,0,0,,already using Safari View
Dialogue: 0,0:01:59.44,0:02:00.03,Default,,0,0,0,,Controller?
Dialogue: 0,0:02:01.63,0:02:03.37,Default,,0,0,0,,Great. If you're already using
Dialogue: 0,0:02:03.37,0:02:05.13,Default,,0,0,0,,Safari View Controller, we have
Dialogue: 0,0:02:05.13,0:02:06.44,Default,,0,0,0,,some improvements to share with
Dialogue: 0,0:02:06.44,0:02:08.60,Default,,0,0,0,,you today that will make Safari
Dialogue: 0,0:02:08.60,0:02:10.00,Default,,0,0,0,,View Controller an even better
Dialogue: 0,0:02:10.00,0:02:11.49,Default,,0,0,0,,experience for your users.
Dialogue: 0,0:02:12.38,0:02:13.81,Default,,0,0,0,,If you aren't using Safari View
Dialogue: 0,0:02:13.81,0:02:15.16,Default,,0,0,0,,Controller but you're providing
Dialogue: 0,0:02:15.16,0:02:17.11,Default,,0,0,0,,one of those experiences, listen
Dialogue: 0,0:02:17.84,0:02:17.91,Default,,0,0,0,,up.
Dialogue: 0,0:02:17.90,0:02:19.13,Default,,0,0,0,,The new APIs that we're going to
Dialogue: 0,0:02:19.17,0:02:21.09,Default,,0,0,0,,talk about today were inspired
Dialogue: 0,0:02:21.09,0:02:23.02,Default,,0,0,0,,by feedback from you, and we
Dialogue: 0,0:02:23.02,0:02:24.23,Default,,0,0,0,,think you'll really like to hear
Dialogue: 0,0:02:24.23,0:02:24.66,Default,,0,0,0,,about it.
Dialogue: 0,0:02:26.95,0:02:28.21,Default,,0,0,0,,Today I'm going to cover
Dialogue: 0,0:02:29.25,0:02:31.15,Default,,0,0,0,,displaying web content on iOS.
Dialogue: 0,0:02:32.61,0:02:33.81,Default,,0,0,0,,Then I'll talk about how to
Dialogue: 0,0:02:33.81,0:02:35.18,Default,,0,0,0,,really match your app's style
Dialogue: 0,0:02:35.18,0:02:36.73,Default,,0,0,0,,using Safari View Controller.
Dialogue: 0,0:02:37.36,0:02:39.67,Default,,0,0,0,,I'll then talk about some
Dialogue: 0,0:02:39.67,0:02:40.95,Default,,0,0,0,,improvements to Safari View
Dialogue: 0,0:02:40.95,0:02:42.53,Default,,0,0,0,,Controller on iOS 11.
Dialogue: 0,0:02:44.10,0:02:45.39,Default,,0,0,0,,Then I'll discuss the new APIs
Dialogue: 0,0:02:45.39,0:02:47.45,Default,,0,0,0,,that have been added to Safari
Dialogue: 0,0:02:47.45,0:02:49.38,Default,,0,0,0,,View Controller to really tailor
Dialogue: 0,0:02:49.38,0:02:51.07,Default,,0,0,0,,it to fit your app's use case.
Dialogue: 0,0:02:53.49,0:02:55.16,Default,,0,0,0,,First, displaying web content.
Dialogue: 0,0:02:55.95,0:02:56.96,Default,,0,0,0,,There are a couple of different
Dialogue: 0,0:02:56.96,0:02:58.37,Default,,0,0,0,,ways, but today I'm going to
Dialogue: 0,0:02:58.37,0:03:00.24,Default,,0,0,0,,talk about two of those, using
Dialogue: 0,0:03:00.24,0:03:02.04,Default,,0,0,0,,SFSafariViewController and using
Dialogue: 0,0:03:02.04,0:03:02.97,Default,,0,0,0,,WKWebView.
Dialogue: 0,0:03:04.22,0:03:05.74,Default,,0,0,0,,To start off, let's talk about
Dialogue: 0,0:03:05.74,0:03:07.18,Default,,0,0,0,,SFSafariViewController.
Dialogue: 0,0:03:08.42,0:03:10.10,Default,,0,0,0,,If you don't know where your
Dialogue: 0,0:03:10.10,0:03:12.45,Default,,0,0,0,,user will be going on the web,
Dialogue: 0,0:03:12.60,0:03:14.20,Default,,0,0,0,,Safari View Controller is really
Dialogue: 0,0:03:14.20,0:03:15.52,Default,,0,0,0,,a good thing for you to use.
Dialogue: 0,0:03:16.29,0:03:17.71,Default,,0,0,0,,It gives you standard browsing
Dialogue: 0,0:03:17.71,0:03:19.20,Default,,0,0,0,,features so you don't need to
Dialogue: 0,0:03:19.20,0:03:20.59,Default,,0,0,0,,worry about implementing an
Dialogue: 0,0:03:20.62,0:03:21.67,Default,,0,0,0,,in-app web browser.
Dialogue: 0,0:03:22.87,0:03:24.09,Default,,0,0,0,,With just a couple lines of
Dialogue: 0,0:03:24.23,0:03:25.88,Default,,0,0,0,,code, you get an in-app web
Dialogue: 0,0:03:25.88,0:03:27.31,Default,,0,0,0,,browser with all of the features
Dialogue: 0,0:03:27.31,0:03:28.65,Default,,0,0,0,,that your users know and love
Dialogue: 0,0:03:28.69,0:03:30.64,Default,,0,0,0,,from Safari in your app.
Dialogue: 0,0:03:32.21,0:03:33.82,Default,,0,0,0,,Safari View Controller is also
Dialogue: 0,0:03:33.82,0:03:34.93,Default,,0,0,0,,great for getting users
Dialogue: 0,0:03:34.93,0:03:36.52,Default,,0,0,0,,authenticated to a third-party
Dialogue: 0,0:03:36.58,0:03:36.86,Default,,0,0,0,,service.
Dialogue: 0,0:03:38.02,0:03:39.68,Default,,0,0,0,,It has the security that users
Dialogue: 0,0:03:39.68,0:03:41.64,Default,,0,0,0,,need while logging in and it has
Dialogue: 0,0:03:41.77,0:03:43.13,Default,,0,0,0,,features that can help them get
Dialogue: 0,0:03:43.13,0:03:44.05,Default,,0,0,0,,logged in quickly.
Dialogue: 0,0:03:44.74,0:03:46.33,Default,,0,0,0,,One main example is Password
Dialogue: 0,0:03:46.33,0:03:47.02,Default,,0,0,0,,AutoFill.
Dialogue: 0,0:03:47.38,0:03:48.50,Default,,0,0,0,,They can quickly fill their
Dialogue: 0,0:03:48.50,0:03:50.45,Default,,0,0,0,,saved passwords from Safari and
Dialogue: 0,0:03:50.45,0:03:51.99,Default,,0,0,0,,log in with a tap of a button.
Dialogue: 0,0:03:54.95,0:03:57.14,Default,,0,0,0,,Now let's talk about WKWebView.
Dialogue: 0,0:03:57.92,0:03:59.57,Default,,0,0,0,,If you don't know the web, or if
Dialogue: 0,0:03:59.57,0:04:00.84,Default,,0,0,0,,you know the content that you'll
Dialogue: 0,0:04:00.84,0:04:02.67,Default,,0,0,0,,be displaying to users ahead of
Dialogue: 0,0:04:02.67,0:04:04.30,Default,,0,0,0,,time, or you even have control
Dialogue: 0,0:04:04.30,0:04:06.56,Default,,0,0,0,,over the web content, WKWebView
Dialogue: 0,0:04:06.56,0:04:07.63,Default,,0,0,0,,might be right for you.
Dialogue: 0,0:04:08.39,0:04:09.81,Default,,0,0,0,,It allows you to manipulate the
Dialogue: 0,0:04:09.81,0:04:11.57,Default,,0,0,0,,DOM using Javascript.
Dialogue: 0,0:04:12.39,0:04:13.68,Default,,0,0,0,,You can also customize
Dialogue: 0,0:04:13.68,0:04:15.77,Default,,0,0,0,,navigations by blocking or
Dialogue: 0,0:04:15.77,0:04:16.71,Default,,0,0,0,,modifying them.
Dialogue: 0,0:04:18.20,0:04:19.85,Default,,0,0,0,,It's a view of web content, so
Dialogue: 0,0:04:19.85,0:04:21.40,Default,,0,0,0,,you can add your own native UI
Dialogue: 0,0:04:21.68,0:04:22.80,Default,,0,0,0,,around the web content.
Dialogue: 0,0:04:23.39,0:04:25.13,Default,,0,0,0,,This is great if part of your
Dialogue: 0,0:04:25.13,0:04:26.65,Default,,0,0,0,,app's UI is implemented using
Dialogue: 0,0:04:26.65,0:04:27.68,Default,,0,0,0,,web technologies.
Dialogue: 0,0:04:28.82,0:04:30.18,Default,,0,0,0,,The web content can blend
Dialogue: 0,0:04:30.30,0:04:31.64,Default,,0,0,0,,seamlessly in with your app's
Dialogue: 0,0:04:31.64,0:04:33.63,Default,,0,0,0,,native UI, so users don't even
Dialogue: 0,0:04:33.63,0:04:35.08,Default,,0,0,0,,need to know that they're
Dialogue: 0,0:04:35.08,0:04:36.39,Default,,0,0,0,,interacting with web content.
Dialogue: 0,0:04:38.47,0:04:39.72,Default,,0,0,0,,But let's get back to Safari
Dialogue: 0,0:04:39.72,0:04:40.84,Default,,0,0,0,,View Controller since I think
Dialogue: 0,0:04:40.84,0:04:41.75,Default,,0,0,0,,that's why you're all here.
Dialogue: 0,0:04:44.14,0:04:45.27,Default,,0,0,0,,Safari View Controller makes
Dialogue: 0,0:04:45.27,0:04:46.62,Default,,0,0,0,,in-app web browsing easy.
Dialogue: 0,0:04:46.69,0:04:48.16,Default,,0,0,0,,As I mentioned before, with just
Dialogue: 0,0:04:48.16,0:04:49.80,Default,,0,0,0,,a couple lines of code, you've
Dialogue: 0,0:04:49.80,0:04:51.57,Default,,0,0,0,,got a fully featured web browser
Dialogue: 0,0:04:51.57,0:04:54.87,Default,,0,0,0,,within your app.
Dialogue: 0,0:04:54.87,0:04:56.50,Default,,0,0,0,,It provides a secure and safe
Dialogue: 0,0:04:56.57,0:04:58.24,Default,,0,0,0,,browsing experience for users.
Dialogue: 0,0:04:59.24,0:05:00.64,Default,,0,0,0,,Let me tell you about a few of
Dialogue: 0,0:05:00.64,0:05:02.29,Default,,0,0,0,,the security features you get
Dialogue: 0,0:05:02.29,0:05:03.52,Default,,0,0,0,,with Safari View Controller.
Dialogue: 0,0:05:04.94,0:05:06.73,Default,,0,0,0,,First, process separation.
Dialogue: 0,0:05:07.43,0:05:08.79,Default,,0,0,0,,There's your app's content and
Dialogue: 0,0:05:08.79,0:05:09.78,Default,,0,0,0,,then there's web content.
Dialogue: 0,0:05:10.83,0:05:12.30,Default,,0,0,0,,Safari View Controller is in a
Dialogue: 0,0:05:12.41,0:05:14.38,Default,,0,0,0,,separate process from your app.
Dialogue: 0,0:05:14.90,0:05:16.88,Default,,0,0,0,,This means that anything that
Dialogue: 0,0:05:16.88,0:05:18.97,Default,,0,0,0,,the user does on the web won't
Dialogue: 0,0:05:18.97,0:05:20.26,Default,,0,0,0,,have an effect on your app's
Dialogue: 0,0:05:20.35,0:05:20.71,Default,,0,0,0,,content.
Dialogue: 0,0:05:21.44,0:05:23.64,Default,,0,0,0,,If they browse to malicious web
Dialogue: 0,0:05:23.68,0:05:25.57,Default,,0,0,0,,page it won't be able to affect
Dialogue: 0,0:05:25.63,0:05:26.39,Default,,0,0,0,,your app's data.
Dialogue: 0,0:05:27.26,0:05:28.42,Default,,0,0,0,,You get out of the business of
Dialogue: 0,0:05:28.42,0:05:30.23,Default,,0,0,0,,taking care of user security on
Dialogue: 0,0:05:30.23,0:05:31.90,Default,,0,0,0,,the web because Safari View
Dialogue: 0,0:05:31.90,0:05:33.30,Default,,0,0,0,,Controller will take care of
Dialogue: 0,0:05:33.30,0:05:34.02,Default,,0,0,0,,that for you.
Dialogue: 0,0:05:34.89,0:05:36.53,Default,,0,0,0,,It provides critical security
Dialogue: 0,0:05:36.56,0:05:37.06,Default,,0,0,0,,features.
Dialogue: 0,0:05:37.27,0:05:39.22,Default,,0,0,0,,Let's talk about a couple of
Dialogue: 0,0:05:39.30,0:05:39.39,Default,,0,0,0,,those.
Dialogue: 0,0:05:41.58,0:05:43.26,Default,,0,0,0,,The lock icon here indicates to
Dialogue: 0,0:05:43.26,0:05:44.35,Default,,0,0,0,,the user that they're browsing
Dialogue: 0,0:05:44.35,0:05:45.69,Default,,0,0,0,,over a secure connection.
Dialogue: 0,0:05:46.13,0:05:47.34,Default,,0,0,0,,This is a really important
Dialogue: 0,0:05:47.39,0:05:48.61,Default,,0,0,0,,feature in a browser.
Dialogue: 0,0:05:49.16,0:05:50.10,Default,,0,0,0,,And you don't need to worry
Dialogue: 0,0:05:50.10,0:05:51.45,Default,,0,0,0,,about implementing it if you use
Dialogue: 0,0:05:51.45,0:05:52.83,Default,,0,0,0,,Safari View Controller for your
Dialogue: 0,0:05:52.83,0:05:53.87,Default,,0,0,0,,in-app web browser.
Dialogue: 0,0:05:55.29,0:05:57.14,Default,,0,0,0,,Safari View Controller will also
Dialogue: 0,0:05:57.14,0:05:58.58,Default,,0,0,0,,warn users if they might be
Dialogue: 0,0:05:58.58,0:06:00.16,Default,,0,0,0,,trying to navigate to a page
Dialogue: 0,0:06:00.16,0:06:01.38,Default,,0,0,0,,that's going to try to steal
Dialogue: 0,0:06:01.38,0:06:02.32,Default,,0,0,0,,their information.
Dialogue: 0,0:06:02.99,0:06:04.55,Default,,0,0,0,,This page is trying to imitate
Dialogue: 0,0:06:04.55,0:06:06.35,Default,,0,0,0,,example.com to get my
Dialogue: 0,0:06:06.42,0:06:07.04,Default,,0,0,0,,information.
Dialogue: 0,0:06:07.04,0:06:09.65,Default,,0,0,0,,And you get features from
Dialogue: 0,0:06:09.65,0:06:10.24,Default,,0,0,0,,Safari.
Dialogue: 0,0:06:10.51,0:06:12.00,Default,,0,0,0,,Let me just highlight a few of
Dialogue: 0,0:06:12.00,0:06:13.14,Default,,0,0,0,,the features that you'll get
Dialogue: 0,0:06:13.26,0:06:14.53,Default,,0,0,0,,with Safari View Controller.
Dialogue: 0,0:06:15.55,0:06:17.77,Default,,0,0,0,,You get AutoFill of passwords,
Dialogue: 0,0:06:17.77,0:06:19.46,Default,,0,0,0,,contact info, and credit cards.
Dialogue: 0,0:06:20.10,0:06:21.95,Default,,0,0,0,,Users can quickly fill out forms
Dialogue: 0,0:06:21.95,0:06:22.54,Default,,0,0,0,,on the web.
Dialogue: 0,0:06:24.55,0:06:26.51,Default,,0,0,0,,Reader is an awesome feature for
Dialogue: 0,0:06:26.51,0:06:27.81,Default,,0,0,0,,decluttering articles on the
Dialogue: 0,0:06:27.81,0:06:28.14,Default,,0,0,0,,web.
Dialogue: 0,0:06:28.63,0:06:30.17,Default,,0,0,0,,Our users of this feature love
Dialogue: 0,0:06:30.17,0:06:31.54,Default,,0,0,0,,it, and they'll love getting to
Dialogue: 0,0:06:31.54,0:06:32.62,Default,,0,0,0,,use it in your app.
Dialogue: 0,0:06:34.67,0:06:36.25,Default,,0,0,0,,ApplePay on the web can help
Dialogue: 0,0:06:36.25,0:06:37.87,Default,,0,0,0,,users quickly make payments
Dialogue: 0,0:06:38.19,0:06:39.88,Default,,0,0,0,,while shopping on the web within
Dialogue: 0,0:06:39.88,0:06:43.16,Default,,0,0,0,,your app.
Dialogue: 0,0:06:43.16,0:06:44.45,Default,,0,0,0,,And users get access to the
Dialogue: 0,0:06:44.45,0:06:46.11,Default,,0,0,0,,Share Sheet that they get
Dialogue: 0,0:06:46.11,0:06:47.16,Default,,0,0,0,,elsewhere on the system.
Dialogue: 0,0:06:47.68,0:06:49.41,Default,,0,0,0,,They get access to some standard
Dialogue: 0,0:06:49.47,0:06:50.54,Default,,0,0,0,,system activities that they
Dialogue: 0,0:06:50.54,0:06:52.11,Default,,0,0,0,,might want to perform, as well
Dialogue: 0,0:06:52.11,0:06:53.84,Default,,0,0,0,,as any third-party extensions
Dialogue: 0,0:06:53.94,0:06:55.29,Default,,0,0,0,,that they have access to in
Dialogue: 0,0:06:55.29,0:06:55.82,Default,,0,0,0,,Safari.
Dialogue: 0,0:06:57.87,0:06:59.20,Default,,0,0,0,,And they get content blocker
Dialogue: 0,0:06:59.20,0:07:00.90,Default,,0,0,0,,extensions that they'd have in
Dialogue: 0,0:07:00.95,0:07:01.47,Default,,0,0,0,,Safari.
Dialogue: 0,0:07:01.99,0:07:02.85,Default,,0,0,0,,This means they won't be
Dialogue: 0,0:07:02.85,0:07:04.31,Default,,0,0,0,,confused about why their
Dialogue: 0,0:07:04.47,0:07:05.77,Default,,0,0,0,,ad-blocker isn't working when
Dialogue: 0,0:07:05.77,0:07:09.33,Default,,0,0,0,,browsing the web in your app.
Dialogue: 0,0:07:09.33,0:07:10.55,Default,,0,0,0,,And there are so many other
Dialogue: 0,0:07:10.55,0:07:12.36,Default,,0,0,0,,features that you get by
Dialogue: 0,0:07:12.36,0:07:13.48,Default,,0,0,0,,implementing Safari View
Dialogue: 0,0:07:13.48,0:07:15.31,Default,,0,0,0,,Controller as your in-app web
Dialogue: 0,0:07:15.34,0:07:15.82,Default,,0,0,0,,browser.
Dialogue: 0,0:07:17.95,0:07:19.57,Default,,0,0,0,,Now, I'd like to talk to you
Dialogue: 0,0:07:19.75,0:07:21.15,Default,,0,0,0,,about how you can better match
Dialogue: 0,0:07:21.15,0:07:23.03,Default,,0,0,0,,your app's style with Safari
Dialogue: 0,0:07:23.03,0:07:24.68,Default,,0,0,0,,View Controller on iOS 11.
Dialogue: 0,0:07:25.16,0:07:26.49,Default,,0,0,0,,There are a couple of new ways.
Dialogue: 0,0:07:27.85,0:07:29.37,Default,,0,0,0,,First, it has a new look.
Dialogue: 0,0:07:30.24,0:07:31.56,Default,,0,0,0,,If you've seen Safari View
Dialogue: 0,0:07:31.56,0:07:33.79,Default,,0,0,0,,Controller prior to iOS 11 you
Dialogue: 0,0:07:33.79,0:07:34.66,Default,,0,0,0,,might have noticed that it
Dialogue: 0,0:07:34.66,0:07:36.05,Default,,0,0,0,,looked a lot like Safari.
Dialogue: 0,0:07:36.78,0:07:38.80,Default,,0,0,0,,Let's take a look on iOS 11.
Dialogue: 0,0:07:39.97,0:07:41.53,Default,,0,0,0,,It looks more like an in-app web
Dialogue: 0,0:07:41.53,0:07:43.18,Default,,0,0,0,,browser so users don't feel like
Dialogue: 0,0:07:43.18,0:07:44.58,Default,,0,0,0,,they've jumped out of your app.
Dialogue: 0,0:07:45.07,0:07:46.73,Default,,0,0,0,,This is the design on iPhone.
Dialogue: 0,0:07:47.80,0:07:49.36,Default,,0,0,0,,It looks great on iPad too.
Dialogue: 0,0:07:51.75,0:07:53.41,Default,,0,0,0,,Now I want to talk to you about
Dialogue: 0,0:07:53.41,0:07:55.25,Default,,0,0,0,,customizing the color of Safari
Dialogue: 0,0:07:55.25,0:07:56.98,Default,,0,0,0,,View Controller so that it fits
Dialogue: 0,0:07:57.02,0:07:58.46,Default,,0,0,0,,with your app's color scheme.
Dialogue: 0,0:07:59.20,0:08:00.85,Default,,0,0,0,,The ability to customize Safari
Dialogue: 0,0:08:00.85,0:08:01.91,Default,,0,0,0,,View Controller's color was
Dialogue: 0,0:08:01.91,0:08:04.36,Default,,0,0,0,,available prior to iOS 11, but
Dialogue: 0,0:08:04.61,0:08:05.84,Default,,0,0,0,,we've made an improvement that I
Dialogue: 0,0:08:05.84,0:08:07.09,Default,,0,0,0,,really want you to know about.
Dialogue: 0,0:08:08.52,0:08:09.63,Default,,0,0,0,,First, let's recap the
Dialogue: 0,0:08:09.63,0:08:10.67,Default,,0,0,0,,customizations.
Dialogue: 0,0:08:11.52,0:08:12.92,Default,,0,0,0,,This is a default Safari View
Dialogue: 0,0:08:12.92,0:08:13.50,Default,,0,0,0,,Controller.
Dialogue: 0,0:08:13.54,0:08:15.13,Default,,0,0,0,,It has the same color scheme as
Dialogue: 0,0:08:15.13,0:08:16.61,Default,,0,0,0,,Safari, blue and white.
Dialogue: 0,0:08:17.16,0:08:18.39,Default,,0,0,0,,But let's say my app has a
Dialogue: 0,0:08:18.39,0:08:19.80,Default,,0,0,0,,different color scheme, black
Dialogue: 0,0:08:19.80,0:08:20.29,Default,,0,0,0,,and aqua.
Dialogue: 0,0:08:22.05,0:08:23.80,Default,,0,0,0,,Here I started using my app's
Dialogue: 0,0:08:23.91,0:08:25.18,Default,,0,0,0,,color scheme in Safari View
Dialogue: 0,0:08:25.18,0:08:25.76,Default,,0,0,0,,Controller.
Dialogue: 0,0:08:25.99,0:08:27.40,Default,,0,0,0,,So, when I present Safari View
Dialogue: 0,0:08:27.40,0:08:28.95,Default,,0,0,0,,Controller to my users it
Dialogue: 0,0:08:28.95,0:08:30.12,Default,,0,0,0,,doesn't feel like they've left
Dialogue: 0,0:08:30.12,0:08:31.37,Default,,0,0,0,,my app.
Dialogue: 0,0:08:31.37,0:08:32.48,Default,,0,0,0,,And it's a really seamless
Dialogue: 0,0:08:32.48,0:08:33.17,Default,,0,0,0,,experience.
Dialogue: 0,0:08:34.93,0:08:36.25,Default,,0,0,0,,You can set these colors by
Dialogue: 0,0:08:36.25,0:08:37.67,Default,,0,0,0,,modifying properties on
Dialogue: 0,0:08:37.71,0:08:39.18,Default,,0,0,0,,SFSafariViewController.
Dialogue: 0,0:08:40.12,0:08:41.79,Default,,0,0,0,,To set the color of bars
Dialogue: 0,0:08:41.84,0:08:43.44,Default,,0,0,0,,surrounding web content you can
Dialogue: 0,0:08:43.44,0:08:45.13,Default,,0,0,0,,use preferredBarTintColor.
Dialogue: 0,0:08:45.90,0:08:47.07,Default,,0,0,0,,And to set the color of the
Dialogue: 0,0:08:47.07,0:08:49.50,Default,,0,0,0,,controls shown here, you can use
Dialogue: 0,0:08:49.54,0:08:51.14,Default,,0,0,0,,preferredControlTintColor.
Dialogue: 0,0:08:51.14,0:08:54.30,Default,,0,0,0,,Now let me tell you about an
Dialogue: 0,0:08:54.30,0:08:55.05,Default,,0,0,0,,improvement to
Dialogue: 0,0:08:55.05,0:08:57.40,Default,,0,0,0,,preferredBarTintColor on iOS 11.
Dialogue: 0,0:08:58.19,0:08:59.11,Default,,0,0,0,,This is my app.
Dialogue: 0,0:08:59.11,0:09:00.41,Default,,0,0,0,,I'm using my favorite shade of
Dialogue: 0,0:09:00.41,0:09:01.63,Default,,0,0,0,,red for its bar color.
Dialogue: 0,0:09:02.89,0:09:04.13,Default,,0,0,0,,Here's what it would look like
Dialogue: 0,0:09:04.13,0:09:05.61,Default,,0,0,0,,if I set that exact same shade
Dialogue: 0,0:09:05.61,0:09:06.79,Default,,0,0,0,,of red to Safari View
Dialogue: 0,0:09:06.79,0:09:09.87,Default,,0,0,0,,Controller's bar color on iOS
Dialogue: 0,0:09:10.50,0:09:10.61,Default,,0,0,0,,10.
Dialogue: 0,0:09:10.82,0:09:12.21,Default,,0,0,0,,As you can see, they don't quite
Dialogue: 0,0:09:12.21,0:09:13.41,Default,,0,0,0,,match up.
Dialogue: 0,0:09:13.62,0:09:15.76,Default,,0,0,0,,And it doesn't feel exactly like
Dialogue: 0,0:09:15.76,0:09:16.59,Default,,0,0,0,,my app.
Dialogue: 0,0:09:16.59,0:09:18.47,Default,,0,0,0,,It looks great, but it's not as
Dialogue: 0,0:09:18.58,0:09:19.50,Default,,0,0,0,,close as it could be.
Dialogue: 0,0:09:20.32,0:09:22.16,Default,,0,0,0,,Let's take a look on iOS 11.
Dialogue: 0,0:09:23.36,0:09:25.01,Default,,0,0,0,,Now, the bar colors match up.
Dialogue: 0,0:09:25.41,0:09:26.68,Default,,0,0,0,,It's just as if I was setting
Dialogue: 0,0:09:26.68,0:09:28.41,Default,,0,0,0,,the bar color on a standard UI
Dialogue: 0,0:09:28.53,0:09:30.44,Default,,0,0,0,,navigation bar or UI toolbar.
Dialogue: 0,0:09:31.06,0:09:32.40,Default,,0,0,0,,So, it looks really great and it
Dialogue: 0,0:09:32.47,0:09:35.83,Default,,0,0,0,,fits well within my app.
Dialogue: 0,0:09:36.62,0:09:38.52,Default,,0,0,0,,Now, I'm delighted to invite my
Dialogue: 0,0:09:38.52,0:09:40.16,Default,,0,0,0,,colleague Louie Livon-Bemel to
Dialogue: 0,0:09:40.16,0:09:41.98,Default,,0,0,0,,the stage to show you just how
Dialogue: 0,0:09:41.98,0:09:43.87,Default,,0,0,0,,easy it is to get Safari View
Dialogue: 0,0:09:43.87,0:09:45.33,Default,,0,0,0,,Controller matching your app's
Dialogue: 0,0:09:45.33,0:09:45.69,Default,,0,0,0,,style.
Dialogue: 0,0:09:46.46,0:09:46.82,Default,,0,0,0,,Thank you.
Dialogue: 0,0:09:47.52,0:09:52.84,Default,,0,0,0,,[ Applause ]
Dialogue: 0,0:09:53.34,0:09:54.19,Default,,0,0,0,,>> Thanks, Chelsea.
Dialogue: 0,0:09:55.32,0:09:57.36,Default,,0,0,0,,Hi, I'm Louie, I'm an engineer
Dialogue: 0,0:09:57.36,0:09:58.99,Default,,0,0,0,,on the Safari team, and I'm
Dialogue: 0,0:09:58.99,0:10:00.58,Default,,0,0,0,,really excited to show you just
Dialogue: 0,0:10:00.58,0:10:02.26,Default,,0,0,0,,how easy it is to customize
Dialogue: 0,0:10:02.26,0:10:03.95,Default,,0,0,0,,Safari View Controller to match
Dialogue: 0,0:10:03.95,0:10:07.61,Default,,0,0,0,,your app style.
Dialogue: 0,0:10:09.80,0:10:10.76,Default,,0,0,0,,I'm working on an all new
Dialogue: 0,0:10:10.76,0:10:12.81,Default,,0,0,0,,version of my app, Pizza Finder.
Dialogue: 0,0:10:13.60,0:10:15.50,Default,,0,0,0,,It's the best app for finding
Dialogue: 0,0:10:15.50,0:10:17.02,Default,,0,0,0,,great pizza near you when you're
Dialogue: 0,0:10:17.02,0:10:18.49,Default,,0,0,0,,working on or even watching a
Dialogue: 0,0:10:18.49,0:10:18.87,Default,,0,0,0,,demo.
Dialogue: 0,0:10:20.53,0:10:22.82,Default,,0,0,0,,Like many of your apps, this app
Dialogue: 0,0:10:22.82,0:10:24.63,Default,,0,0,0,,uses a standard UI Navigation
Dialogue: 0,0:10:24.63,0:10:25.20,Default,,0,0,0,,Controller.
Dialogue: 0,0:10:25.64,0:10:27.18,Default,,0,0,0,,I've got a list of pizza places
Dialogue: 0,0:10:27.18,0:10:29.40,Default,,0,0,0,,here, and when I tap one, a new
Dialogue: 0,0:10:29.40,0:10:31.22,Default,,0,0,0,,view comes in from right to left
Dialogue: 0,0:10:31.22,0:10:32.37,Default,,0,0,0,,with more details.
Dialogue: 0,0:10:33.45,0:10:34.99,Default,,0,0,0,,The default presentation of
Dialogue: 0,0:10:34.99,0:10:37.14,Default,,0,0,0,,Safari View Controller is a lot
Dialogue: 0,0:10:37.14,0:10:37.81,Default,,0,0,0,,like this.
Dialogue: 0,0:10:38.33,0:10:39.48,Default,,0,0,0,,When I tap on the website,
Dialogue: 0,0:10:40.22,0:10:41.83,Default,,0,0,0,,Safari View Controller came in
Dialogue: 0,0:10:41.93,0:10:44.94,Default,,0,0,0,,from right to left just like a
Dialogue: 0,0:10:44.94,0:10:46.17,Default,,0,0,0,,UI Navigation Controller.
Dialogue: 0,0:10:46.94,0:10:48.49,Default,,0,0,0,,Users can even interactively
Dialogue: 0,0:10:48.49,0:10:49.57,Default,,0,0,0,,edge swipe back when they're
Dialogue: 0,0:10:49.57,0:10:50.21,Default,,0,0,0,,done browsing.
Dialogue: 0,0:10:51.87,0:10:52.66,Default,,0,0,0,,So, this is great.
Dialogue: 0,0:10:52.75,0:10:56.12,Default,,0,0,0,,I have a very standard UI here
Dialogue: 0,0:10:56.42,0:10:57.65,Default,,0,0,0,,that my users are used to from
Dialogue: 0,0:10:57.65,0:10:59.71,Default,,0,0,0,,Safari and any other app that's
Dialogue: 0,0:10:59.71,0:11:01.04,Default,,0,0,0,,using Safari View Controller on
Dialogue: 0,0:11:01.04,0:11:01.61,Default,,0,0,0,,the system.
Dialogue: 0,0:11:03.65,0:11:05.33,Default,,0,0,0,,Users even get really advanced
Dialogue: 0,0:11:05.33,0:11:07.44,Default,,0,0,0,,features like in the Share Sheet
Dialogue: 0,0:11:07.44,0:11:08.54,Default,,0,0,0,,all the activities they're used
Dialogue: 0,0:11:08.54,0:11:10.48,Default,,0,0,0,,to from Safari and the powerful
Dialogue: 0,0:11:10.48,0:11:11.85,Default,,0,0,0,,third-party extensions that
Dialogue: 0,0:11:11.85,0:11:12.70,Default,,0,0,0,,they're used to using.
Dialogue: 0,0:11:14.02,0:11:15.28,Default,,0,0,0,,However, this isn't perfect.
Dialogue: 0,0:11:16.16,0:11:17.25,Default,,0,0,0,,It sort of feels like you're
Dialogue: 0,0:11:17.25,0:11:18.25,Default,,0,0,0,,somewhere else.
Dialogue: 0,0:11:18.57,0:11:20.24,Default,,0,0,0,,You might be in another app or
Dialogue: 0,0:11:20.42,0:11:21.70,Default,,0,0,0,,somewhere else on the system or
Dialogue: 0,0:11:21.70,0:11:23.49,Default,,0,0,0,,somewhere else in my app, it
Dialogue: 0,0:11:23.49,0:11:25.16,Default,,0,0,0,,doesn't, it's not clear that
Dialogue: 0,0:11:25.16,0:11:26.13,Default,,0,0,0,,you're still within Pizza
Dialogue: 0,0:11:26.13,0:11:26.60,Default,,0,0,0,,Finder.
Dialogue: 0,0:11:27.19,0:11:28.26,Default,,0,0,0,,So, I want to show you how to
Dialogue: 0,0:11:28.26,0:11:29.04,Default,,0,0,0,,improve this.
Dialogue: 0,0:11:29.54,0:11:32.29,Default,,0,0,0,,Here's where I'm presenting
Dialogue: 0,0:11:32.29,0:11:33.52,Default,,0,0,0,,Safari View Controller in my
Dialogue: 0,0:11:33.52,0:11:33.78,Default,,0,0,0,,app.
Dialogue: 0,0:11:33.95,0:11:34.96,Default,,0,0,0,,It's really simple.
Dialogue: 0,0:11:35.12,0:11:36.36,Default,,0,0,0,,All you need to do to adopt
Dialogue: 0,0:11:36.36,0:11:38.04,Default,,0,0,0,,Safari View Controller is do two
Dialogue: 0,0:11:38.04,0:11:38.58,Default,,0,0,0,,things.
Dialogue: 0,0:11:39.10,0:11:40.36,Default,,0,0,0,,The first one, is create a
Dialogue: 0,0:11:40.36,0:11:42.60,Default,,0,0,0,,Safari View Controller using the
Dialogue: 0,0:11:42.60,0:11:44.18,Default,,0,0,0,,URL that you want to lead to.
Dialogue: 0,0:11:46.01,0:11:47.36,Default,,0,0,0,,The second thing you need to do
Dialogue: 0,0:11:47.47,0:11:48.17,Default,,0,0,0,,is present it.
Dialogue: 0,0:11:48.17,0:11:49.62,Default,,0,0,0,,And that's it, that's how you
Dialogue: 0,0:11:49.62,0:11:50.81,Default,,0,0,0,,adapt Safari View Controller.
Dialogue: 0,0:11:51.68,0:11:53.36,Default,,0,0,0,,But let's make a few changes.
Dialogue: 0,0:11:53.99,0:11:57.89,Default,,0,0,0,,So, I've done two different
Dialogue: 0,0:11:57.89,0:11:58.32,Default,,0,0,0,,things here.
Dialogue: 0,0:11:58.91,0:12:00.52,Default,,0,0,0,,The first one is setting the
Dialogue: 0,0:12:00.52,0:12:02.48,Default,,0,0,0,,preferredBarTintColor to the
Dialogue: 0,0:12:02.48,0:12:03.61,Default,,0,0,0,,same bar color I'm using
Dialogue: 0,0:12:03.61,0:12:04.41,Default,,0,0,0,,elsewhere in my app.
Dialogue: 0,0:12:04.95,0:12:06.20,Default,,0,0,0,,In this case it's that orangish
Dialogue: 0,0:12:06.20,0:12:06.77,Default,,0,0,0,,red color.
Dialogue: 0,0:12:08.10,0:12:09.67,Default,,0,0,0,,Second thing I'm doing is
Dialogue: 0,0:12:09.67,0:12:09.99,Default,,0,0,0,,setting the
Dialogue: 0,0:12:09.99,0:12:11.85,Default,,0,0,0,,preferredControlTintColor to the
Dialogue: 0,0:12:11.85,0:12:13.38,Default,,0,0,0,,same control color I'm using
Dialogue: 0,0:12:13.38,0:12:14.90,Default,,0,0,0,,elsewhere in my app, in this
Dialogue: 0,0:12:14.90,0:12:15.68,Default,,0,0,0,,case that's white.
Dialogue: 0,0:12:17.03,0:12:18.14,Default,,0,0,0,,So, I'll rebuild and I'll show
Dialogue: 0,0:12:18.14,0:12:19.56,Default,,0,0,0,,you how these changes affect
Dialogue: 0,0:12:19.56,0:12:20.22,Default,,0,0,0,,Pizza Finder.
Dialogue: 0,0:12:26.29,0:12:27.20,Default,,0,0,0,,Now when I look at a pizza
Dialogue: 0,0:12:27.20,0:12:29.14,Default,,0,0,0,,place, and go to their website,
Dialogue: 0,0:12:30.01,0:12:31.45,Default,,0,0,0,,Safari View Controller matches
Dialogue: 0,0:12:31.45,0:12:33.02,Default,,0,0,0,,my app's branding and it's
Dialogue: 0,0:12:33.02,0:12:34.33,Default,,0,0,0,,really obvious that I'm still
Dialogue: 0,0:12:34.33,0:12:35.46,Default,,0,0,0,,within Pizza Finder.
Dialogue: 0,0:12:35.58,0:12:36.37,Default,,0,0,0,,It doesn't feel like I'm
Dialogue: 0,0:12:36.37,0:12:37.17,Default,,0,0,0,,somewhere else.
Dialogue: 0,0:12:38.22,0:12:39.65,Default,,0,0,0,,That's just how easy it is to
Dialogue: 0,0:12:39.65,0:12:41.26,Default,,0,0,0,,customize Safari View Controller
Dialogue: 0,0:12:41.51,0:12:43.00,Default,,0,0,0,,to match your app style and get
Dialogue: 0,0:12:43.00,0:12:44.09,Default,,0,0,0,,your app's branding.
Dialogue: 0,0:12:44.45,0:12:45.72,Default,,0,0,0,,Thank you so much, and I'll now
Dialogue: 0,0:12:45.72,0:12:46.75,Default,,0,0,0,,hand it back over to Chelsea.
Dialogue: 0,0:12:48.52,0:12:53.06,Default,,0,0,0,,[ Applause ]
Dialogue: 0,0:12:53.56,0:12:54.28,Default,,0,0,0,,>> Thanks, Louie.
Dialogue: 0,0:12:55.40,0:12:57.19,Default,,0,0,0,,Louie just showed you how easy
Dialogue: 0,0:12:57.19,0:12:59.35,Default,,0,0,0,,it is to get his app's branding
Dialogue: 0,0:12:59.35,0:13:00.67,Default,,0,0,0,,in Safari View Controller.
Dialogue: 0,0:13:01.24,0:13:02.41,Default,,0,0,0,,With just a couple lines of
Dialogue: 0,0:13:02.41,0:13:03.72,Default,,0,0,0,,code, he had Safari View
Dialogue: 0,0:13:03.72,0:13:05.10,Default,,0,0,0,,Controller up and running with
Dialogue: 0,0:13:05.10,0:13:06.45,Default,,0,0,0,,his app's color scheme.
Dialogue: 0,0:13:08.25,0:13:09.90,Default,,0,0,0,,We can't wait to see how good
Dialogue: 0,0:13:09.98,0:13:11.44,Default,,0,0,0,,Safari View Controller's color
Dialogue: 0,0:13:11.44,0:13:14.87,Default,,0,0,0,,schemes look on your app.
Dialogue: 0,0:13:15.14,0:13:17.13,Default,,0,0,0,,Now, I'd like to talk to you
Dialogue: 0,0:13:17.48,0:13:18.65,Default,,0,0,0,,about some improvements that
Dialogue: 0,0:13:18.65,0:13:19.75,Default,,0,0,0,,we've made to Safari View
Dialogue: 0,0:13:19.75,0:13:21.48,Default,,0,0,0,,Controller on iOS 11.
Dialogue: 0,0:13:22.38,0:13:24.17,Default,,0,0,0,,There are five key improvements
Dialogue: 0,0:13:24.22,0:13:25.45,Default,,0,0,0,,that I'm going to talk about.
Dialogue: 0,0:13:27.57,0:13:29.33,Default,,0,0,0,,You may have heard about the new
Dialogue: 0,0:13:29.40,0:13:31.22,Default,,0,0,0,,feature on iOS 11, Drag and
Dialogue: 0,0:13:31.22,0:13:31.49,Default,,0,0,0,,Drop.
Dialogue: 0,0:13:32.32,0:13:34.01,Default,,0,0,0,,I'm excited to let you know that
Dialogue: 0,0:13:34.01,0:13:36.10,Default,,0,0,0,,on iOS 11, Safari View
Dialogue: 0,0:13:36.10,0:13:37.86,Default,,0,0,0,,Controller has Drag and Drop out
Dialogue: 0,0:13:37.86,0:13:38.45,Default,,0,0,0,,of the box.
Dialogue: 0,0:13:38.86,0:13:40.93,Default,,0,0,0,,Users can easily drag URLs out
Dialogue: 0,0:13:40.93,0:13:42.61,Default,,0,0,0,,of Safari View Controller into
Dialogue: 0,0:13:43.65,0:13:45.28,Default,,0,0,0,,other apps.
Dialogue: 0,0:13:45.52,0:13:46.69,Default,,0,0,0,,Now I'd like to talk to you
Dialogue: 0,0:13:46.69,0:13:48.59,Default,,0,0,0,,about some improvements to how
Dialogue: 0,0:13:48.59,0:13:50.32,Default,,0,0,0,,Status Bar styling works in
Dialogue: 0,0:13:50.32,0:13:51.49,Default,,0,0,0,,Safari View Controller.
Dialogue: 0,0:13:54.04,0:13:55.35,Default,,0,0,0,,When presenting Safari View
Dialogue: 0,0:13:55.35,0:13:56.80,Default,,0,0,0,,Controller in some apps, the
Dialogue: 0,0:13:56.80,0:13:58.49,Default,,0,0,0,,Status Bar can become difficult
Dialogue: 0,0:13:58.49,0:13:58.88,Default,,0,0,0,,to read.
Dialogue: 0,0:14:00.44,0:14:01.98,Default,,0,0,0,,It's hard to even notice here,
Dialogue: 0,0:14:02.03,0:14:03.97,Default,,0,0,0,,but I have a dark purple bar,
Dialogue: 0,0:14:03.97,0:14:05.85,Default,,0,0,0,,with a black Status Bar text on
Dialogue: 0,0:14:05.85,0:14:07.52,Default,,0,0,0,,top, and it's illegible.
Dialogue: 0,0:14:09.40,0:14:11.30,Default,,0,0,0,,Ideally, you'd want white Status
Dialogue: 0,0:14:11.30,0:14:13.39,Default,,0,0,0,,Bar text so that the user can
Dialogue: 0,0:14:13.39,0:14:15.96,Default,,0,0,0,,easily read the Status Bar, but
Dialogue: 0,0:14:16.26,0:14:17.95,Default,,0,0,0,,if you just hard code a specific
Dialogue: 0,0:14:18.01,0:14:19.75,Default,,0,0,0,,Status Bar style, you're not
Dialogue: 0,0:14:20.00,0:14:21.45,Default,,0,0,0,,fully fixing the problem.
Dialogue: 0,0:14:21.51,0:14:25.18,Default,,0,0,0,,Other views can be presented in
Dialogue: 0,0:14:25.18,0:14:27.16,Default,,0,0,0,,Safari View Controller such as
Dialogue: 0,0:14:27.16,0:14:29.26,Default,,0,0,0,,the Messages extension, or a
Dialogue: 0,0:14:29.32,0:14:30.28,Default,,0,0,0,,full-screen video.
Dialogue: 0,0:14:31.29,0:14:32.81,Default,,0,0,0,,Here the user is sharing to
Dialogue: 0,0:14:32.81,0:14:35.47,Default,,0,0,0,,Messages so the white Status Bar
Dialogue: 0,0:14:35.47,0:14:37.55,Default,,0,0,0,,style that's been hard coded is
Dialogue: 0,0:14:37.55,0:14:39.16,Default,,0,0,0,,illegible over the white bar of
Dialogue: 0,0:14:39.16,0:14:40.20,Default,,0,0,0,,the Messages view.
Dialogue: 0,0:14:40.80,0:14:44.72,Default,,0,0,0,,The bottom line is that other
Dialogue: 0,0:14:44.72,0:14:46.68,Default,,0,0,0,,views can be presented in Safari
Dialogue: 0,0:14:46.68,0:14:47.40,Default,,0,0,0,,View Controller.
Dialogue: 0,0:14:48.95,0:14:50.11,Default,,0,0,0,,Safari View Controller has
Dialogue: 0,0:14:50.11,0:14:52.01,Default,,0,0,0,,improvements to better adapt the
Dialogue: 0,0:14:52.09,0:14:53.87,Default,,0,0,0,,Status Bar style when other
Dialogue: 0,0:14:53.87,0:14:56.04,Default,,0,0,0,,views are presented on iOS 11.
Dialogue: 0,0:14:57.07,0:14:58.81,Default,,0,0,0,,In order to allow this to work,
Dialogue: 0,0:14:59.06,0:14:59.85,Default,,0,0,0,,you'll want to use
Dialogue: 0,0:14:59.85,0:15:01.44,Default,,0,0,0,,UIViewController-based Status
Dialogue: 0,0:15:01.51,0:15:02.16,Default,,0,0,0,,Bar appearance.
Dialogue: 0,0:15:03.00,0:15:04.31,Default,,0,0,0,,This has been the recommendation
Dialogue: 0,0:15:04.31,0:15:06.58,Default,,0,0,0,,for all apps since iOS 7.
Dialogue: 0,0:15:07.54,0:15:08.80,Default,,0,0,0,,To do this, you can set
Dialogue: 0,0:15:08.80,0:15:10.26,Default,,0,0,0,,UIViewControllerBased
Dialogue: 0,0:15:10.26,0:15:12.11,Default,,0,0,0,,StatusBarAppearance to yes in
Dialogue: 0,0:15:12.11,0:15:13.36,Default,,0,0,0,,your app's Info.plist.
Dialogue: 0,0:15:14.64,0:15:16.09,Default,,0,0,0,,This will ensure that the Status
Dialogue: 0,0:15:16.12,0:15:17.77,Default,,0,0,0,,Bar remains legible even when
Dialogue: 0,0:15:17.77,0:15:19.29,Default,,0,0,0,,other views are presented in
Dialogue: 0,0:15:19.29,0:15:20.33,Default,,0,0,0,,Safari View Controller.
Dialogue: 0,0:15:20.33,0:15:24.16,Default,,0,0,0,,Now I'd like to tell you about
Dialogue: 0,0:15:24.16,0:15:26.11,Default,,0,0,0,,another improvement, but it
Dialogue: 0,0:15:26.11,0:15:27.62,Default,,0,0,0,,requires a bit of background.
Dialogue: 0,0:15:28.11,0:15:30.05,Default,,0,0,0,,So, I'd like to explain a
Dialogue: 0,0:15:30.11,0:15:31.74,Default,,0,0,0,,scenario in Safari to start.
Dialogue: 0,0:15:32.97,0:15:34.63,Default,,0,0,0,,A common experience on the web
Dialogue: 0,0:15:34.88,0:15:36.28,Default,,0,0,0,,is checkout with a third-party
Dialogue: 0,0:15:36.28,0:15:36.73,Default,,0,0,0,,service.
Dialogue: 0,0:15:37.53,0:15:39.19,Default,,0,0,0,,Here I have a page that's asking
Dialogue: 0,0:15:39.19,0:15:40.84,Default,,0,0,0,,me to checkout using Example
Dialogue: 0,0:15:40.84,0:15:41.34,Default,,0,0,0,,Checkout.
Dialogue: 0,0:15:41.85,0:15:45.99,Default,,0,0,0,,When I tap buy now in Safari, a
Dialogue: 0,0:15:45.99,0:15:48.26,Default,,0,0,0,,new tab is opened and I'm able
Dialogue: 0,0:15:48.33,0:15:49.52,Default,,0,0,0,,to complete my payment.
Dialogue: 0,0:15:51.25,0:15:53.63,Default,,0,0,0,,When I tap Buy Now on Example
Dialogue: 0,0:15:53.63,0:15:56.32,Default,,0,0,0,,Checkout, I -- and complete my
Dialogue: 0,0:15:56.40,0:15:59.53,Default,,0,0,0,,payment, the tab that was opened
Dialogue: 0,0:15:59.53,0:16:01.01,Default,,0,0,0,,is closed and I'm back on the
Dialogue: 0,0:16:01.13,0:16:02.47,Default,,0,0,0,,store site that I was on.
Dialogue: 0,0:16:02.98,0:16:04.07,Default,,0,0,0,,And the store knows that I've
Dialogue: 0,0:16:04.07,0:16:05.56,Default,,0,0,0,,completed my payment.
Dialogue: 0,0:16:06.54,0:16:07.65,Default,,0,0,0,,This is an example of what
Dialogue: 0,0:16:07.65,0:16:09.33,Default,,0,0,0,,happens when a webpage calls
Dialogue: 0,0:16:09.33,0:16:11.47,Default,,0,0,0,,window.open and subsequently
Dialogue: 0,0:16:11.47,0:16:12.74,Default,,0,0,0,,calls window.close.
Dialogue: 0,0:16:13.72,0:16:15.25,Default,,0,0,0,,It previously wasn't supported
Dialogue: 0,0:16:15.25,0:16:16.45,Default,,0,0,0,,in Safari View Controller
Dialogue: 0,0:16:16.45,0:16:17.67,Default,,0,0,0,,because Safari View Controller
Dialogue: 0,0:16:17.67,0:16:18.66,Default,,0,0,0,,doesn't have tabs.
Dialogue: 0,0:16:19.44,0:16:21.48,Default,,0,0,0,,But on iOS 11 Safari View
Dialogue: 0,0:16:21.48,0:16:23.35,Default,,0,0,0,,Controller supports window.open.
Dialogue: 0,0:16:23.78,0:16:27.06,Default,,0,0,0,,[applause] It's pretty great,
Dialogue: 0,0:16:28.85,0:16:29.27,Default,,0,0,0,,yeah.
Dialogue: 0,0:16:29.52,0:16:31.71,Default,,0,0,0,,The way that this now works is
Dialogue: 0,0:16:32.16,0:16:34.41,Default,,0,0,0,,in Safari View Controller when I
Dialogue: 0,0:16:34.48,0:16:37.31,Default,,0,0,0,,tap Buy Now a new, I've
Dialogue: 0,0:16:37.31,0:16:39.08,Default,,0,0,0,,navigated forward instead of
Dialogue: 0,0:16:39.08,0:16:39.86,Default,,0,0,0,,opening a new tab.
Dialogue: 0,0:16:41.19,0:16:42.97,Default,,0,0,0,,Once I've completed my payment
Dialogue: 0,0:16:43.10,0:16:45.22,Default,,0,0,0,,after tapping Buy Now, I'm
Dialogue: 0,0:16:45.38,0:16:47.67,Default,,0,0,0,,navigated back to the page, the
Dialogue: 0,0:16:47.67,0:16:50.24,Default,,0,0,0,,domain I was on and the page
Dialogue: 0,0:16:50.24,0:16:51.63,Default,,0,0,0,,knows that I've completed my
Dialogue: 0,0:16:51.63,0:16:52.17,Default,,0,0,0,,payment.
Dialogue: 0,0:16:53.05,0:16:54.33,Default,,0,0,0,,So, I get a confirmation in
Dialogue: 0,0:16:54.33,0:16:55.49,Default,,0,0,0,,Safari View Controller.
Dialogue: 0,0:16:56.59,0:16:58.35,Default,,0,0,0,,This is new to iOS 11.
Dialogue: 0,0:17:00.58,0:17:02.13,Default,,0,0,0,,Now I'd like to talk about some
Dialogue: 0,0:17:02.13,0:17:05.03,Default,,0,0,0,,privacy improvements on iOS 11
Dialogue: 0,0:17:05.45,0:17:06.61,Default,,0,0,0,,in Safari View Controller.
Dialogue: 0,0:17:09.39,0:17:11.13,Default,,0,0,0,,Browsing the web in your app is
Dialogue: 0,0:17:11.13,0:17:12.28,Default,,0,0,0,,different than browsing the web
Dialogue: 0,0:17:12.28,0:17:13.07,Default,,0,0,0,,in other apps.
Dialogue: 0,0:17:13.94,0:17:15.12,Default,,0,0,0,,It's different than browsing the
Dialogue: 0,0:17:15.12,0:17:16.25,Default,,0,0,0,,web in Safari.
Dialogue: 0,0:17:17.03,0:17:19.58,Default,,0,0,0,,I sometimes want to use
Dialogue: 0,0:17:19.65,0:17:21.00,Default,,0,0,0,,different accounts when browsing
Dialogue: 0,0:17:21.00,0:17:21.94,Default,,0,0,0,,the web in different apps.
Dialogue: 0,0:17:22.90,0:17:24.47,Default,,0,0,0,,For some apps, I'll use my work
Dialogue: 0,0:17:24.47,0:17:25.79,Default,,0,0,0,,account and for other apps I'll
Dialogue: 0,0:17:25.79,0:17:27.03,Default,,0,0,0,,use my personal account.
Dialogue: 0,0:17:28.21,0:17:30.46,Default,,0,0,0,,On iOS 11, Safari View
Dialogue: 0,0:17:30.46,0:17:31.79,Default,,0,0,0,,Controller will have a separate
Dialogue: 0,0:17:31.79,0:17:34.16,Default,,0,0,0,,persistent data store in each
Dialogue: 0,0:17:34.48,0:17:35.60,Default,,0,0,0,,app that it's used in.
Dialogue: 0,0:17:36.33,0:17:38.18,Default,,0,0,0,,This means that cookies, local
Dialogue: 0,0:17:38.25,0:17:39.82,Default,,0,0,0,,storage, and other browsing data
Dialogue: 0,0:17:40.35,0:17:41.73,Default,,0,0,0,,will be contained within your
Dialogue: 0,0:17:42.05,0:17:43.49,Default,,0,0,0,,app and scoped to your app.
Dialogue: 0,0:17:44.82,0:17:46.97,Default,,0,0,0,,And this means that the user
Dialogue: 0,0:17:46.97,0:17:48.53,Default,,0,0,0,,won't automatically be logged in
Dialogue: 0,0:17:48.53,0:17:49.86,Default,,0,0,0,,to whatever accounts they were
Dialogue: 0,0:17:49.86,0:17:51.33,Default,,0,0,0,,logged into in Safari.
Dialogue: 0,0:17:52.01,0:17:54.48,Default,,0,0,0,,What this does is it will
Dialogue: 0,0:17:54.48,0:17:56.46,Default,,0,0,0,,prevent cross-app tracking of
Dialogue: 0,0:17:56.46,0:17:58.50,Default,,0,0,0,,user's browsing activity that
Dialogue: 0,0:17:58.50,0:18:00.22,Default,,0,0,0,,you and your users may not have
Dialogue: 0,0:18:00.22,0:18:01.33,Default,,0,0,0,,even been aware about.
Dialogue: 0,0:18:02.01,0:18:04.01,Default,,0,0,0,,And ultimately, it helps keep
Dialogue: 0,0:18:04.01,0:18:06.04,Default,,0,0,0,,users' browsing activity private
Dialogue: 0,0:18:06.31,0:18:08.63,Default,,0,0,0,,and scoped within your app.
Dialogue: 0,0:18:09.85,0:18:11.46,Default,,0,0,0,,Now I'd like to talk about a
Dialogue: 0,0:18:11.46,0:18:13.09,Default,,0,0,0,,change to Private Browsing in
Dialogue: 0,0:18:13.09,0:18:14.27,Default,,0,0,0,,Safari View Controller.
Dialogue: 0,0:18:15.46,0:18:16.83,Default,,0,0,0,,Now that Safari View Controller
Dialogue: 0,0:18:16.83,0:18:19.13,Default,,0,0,0,,has its own separate persistent
Dialogue: 0,0:18:19.13,0:18:21.43,Default,,0,0,0,,data store for each app, it's
Dialogue: 0,0:18:21.43,0:18:23.03,Default,,0,0,0,,browsing mode is no longer tied
Dialogue: 0,0:18:23.03,0:18:25.50,Default,,0,0,0,,to Safari's this means that I
Dialogue: 0,0:18:25.50,0:18:27.21,Default,,0,0,0,,now longer get the following
Dialogue: 0,0:18:27.35,0:18:28.61,Default,,0,0,0,,frustrating experience.
Dialogue: 0,0:18:29.82,0:18:31.58,Default,,0,0,0,,I'm browsing the web in Safari
Dialogue: 0,0:18:31.66,0:18:33.95,Default,,0,0,0,,in Private Mode.
Dialogue: 0,0:18:34.16,0:18:37.24,Default,,0,0,0,,Time passes and later that day
Dialogue: 0,0:18:37.58,0:18:38.87,Default,,0,0,0,,after I've forgotten that I was
Dialogue: 0,0:18:38.87,0:18:41.12,Default,,0,0,0,,even in Private Mode, I go to my
Dialogue: 0,0:18:41.12,0:18:42.89,Default,,0,0,0,,favorite app that opens links
Dialogue: 0,0:18:42.89,0:18:44.30,Default,,0,0,0,,using Safari View Controller.
Dialogue: 0,0:18:45.69,0:18:46.85,Default,,0,0,0,,Safari View Controller is
Dialogue: 0,0:18:46.88,0:18:49.18,Default,,0,0,0,,presented in Private Mode once I
Dialogue: 0,0:18:49.18,0:18:51.31,Default,,0,0,0,,open a link and that's confusing
Dialogue: 0,0:18:51.31,0:18:52.31,Default,,0,0,0,,to me because I didn't
Dialogue: 0,0:18:52.31,0:18:54.12,Default,,0,0,0,,intentionally tell it to open in
Dialogue: 0,0:18:54.12,0:18:55.12,Default,,0,0,0,,Private Browsing Mode.
Dialogue: 0,0:18:56.29,0:18:58.14,Default,,0,0,0,,So, on iOS 11 now that Safari
Dialogue: 0,0:18:58.14,0:18:59.80,Default,,0,0,0,,View Controller has its own
Dialogue: 0,0:19:00.55,0:19:02.50,Default,,0,0,0,,browsing mode, it's no longer
Dialogue: 0,0:19:02.64,0:19:03.73,Default,,0,0,0,,tied to Safari's.
Dialogue: 0,0:19:04.86,0:19:06.56,Default,,0,0,0,,That means that your apps' color
Dialogue: 0,0:19:06.56,0:19:08.45,Default,,0,0,0,,scheme will be used more often.
Dialogue: 0,0:19:08.45,0:19:14.02,Default,,0,0,0,,Now I'd like to tell you about
Dialogue: 0,0:19:14.09,0:19:15.79,Default,,0,0,0,,three new APIs that we've added
Dialogue: 0,0:19:16.24,0:19:17.92,Default,,0,0,0,,so you can really tailor Safari
Dialogue: 0,0:19:17.92,0:19:19.73,Default,,0,0,0,,View Controller to fit your
Dialogue: 0,0:19:20.04,0:19:20.92,Default,,0,0,0,,app's experience.
Dialogue: 0,0:19:22.96,0:19:24.56,Default,,0,0,0,,First I'd like to talk to about
Dialogue: 0,0:19:24.56,0:19:25.93,Default,,0,0,0,,how you can now customize the
Dialogue: 0,0:19:25.93,0:19:27.56,Default,,0,0,0,,Dismiss button of Safari View
Dialogue: 0,0:19:27.56,0:19:28.15,Default,,0,0,0,,Controller.
Dialogue: 0,0:19:28.64,0:19:31.83,Default,,0,0,0,,Language is very important when
Dialogue: 0,0:19:31.83,0:19:33.44,Default,,0,0,0,,conveying intent to the user.
Dialogue: 0,0:19:34.81,0:19:36.18,Default,,0,0,0,,The standard Dismiss button
Dialogue: 0,0:19:36.18,0:19:38.18,Default,,0,0,0,,style for Safari View Controller
Dialogue: 0,0:19:38.25,0:19:38.79,Default,,0,0,0,,is Done.
Dialogue: 0,0:19:39.66,0:19:40.91,Default,,0,0,0,,This works really well for a
Dialogue: 0,0:19:41.01,0:19:42.41,Default,,0,0,0,,standard browsing case, because
Dialogue: 0,0:19:42.41,0:19:43.54,Default,,0,0,0,,the user can browse through a
Dialogue: 0,0:19:43.54,0:19:45.01,Default,,0,0,0,,bunch of different web pages and
Dialogue: 0,0:19:45.24,0:19:46.22,Default,,0,0,0,,then when they're finished
Dialogue: 0,0:19:46.22,0:19:48.17,Default,,0,0,0,,browsing tap Done to indicate
Dialogue: 0,0:19:48.17,0:19:48.88,Default,,0,0,0,,that they've ended their
Dialogue: 0,0:19:48.88,0:19:49.80,Default,,0,0,0,,browsing session.
Dialogue: 0,0:19:51.87,0:19:53.90,Default,,0,0,0,,On iOS 11 we've added two new
Dialogue: 0,0:19:53.90,0:19:55.61,Default,,0,0,0,,options that this Dismiss button
Dialogue: 0,0:19:55.61,0:19:56.39,Default,,0,0,0,,can take on.
Dialogue: 0,0:19:57.29,0:19:58.86,Default,,0,0,0,,The first of those options is
Dialogue: 0,0:19:58.86,0:19:59.42,Default,,0,0,0,,Cancel.
Dialogue: 0,0:20:00.43,0:20:01.93,Default,,0,0,0,,I think Cancel makes a lot of
Dialogue: 0,0:20:01.99,0:20:03.32,Default,,0,0,0,,sense when I'm getting my user's
Dialogue: 0,0:20:03.32,0:20:04.95,Default,,0,0,0,,authenticated to a third-party
Dialogue: 0,0:20:04.95,0:20:05.40,Default,,0,0,0,,service.
Dialogue: 0,0:20:06.39,0:20:07.87,Default,,0,0,0,,The user will know that if they
Dialogue: 0,0:20:07.87,0:20:09.52,Default,,0,0,0,,tap that button, they're not
Dialogue: 0,0:20:09.52,0:20:10.73,Default,,0,0,0,,really authenticating with my
Dialogue: 0,0:20:10.81,0:20:12.34,Default,,0,0,0,,service, they're cancelling the
Dialogue: 0,0:20:12.34,0:20:13.13,Default,,0,0,0,,transaction.
Dialogue: 0,0:20:14.31,0:20:16.34,Default,,0,0,0,,The other new style is Close.
Dialogue: 0,0:20:17.29,0:20:18.36,Default,,0,0,0,,This makes sense if I'm
Dialogue: 0,0:20:18.36,0:20:19.78,Default,,0,0,0,,presenting some transient web
Dialogue: 0,0:20:19.78,0:20:21.65,Default,,0,0,0,,content to the user, perhaps a
Dialogue: 0,0:20:21.65,0:20:23.10,Default,,0,0,0,,Terms of Service page.
Dialogue: 0,0:20:24.34,0:20:25.44,Default,,0,0,0,,I'm giving them a page where
Dialogue: 0,0:20:25.44,0:20:26.49,Default,,0,0,0,,they're probably not likely to
Dialogue: 0,0:20:26.49,0:20:28.32,Default,,0,0,0,,follow other links, so they'll
Dialogue: 0,0:20:28.32,0:20:30.33,Default,,0,0,0,,just Close once they've finished
Dialogue: 0,0:20:30.33,0:20:34.94,Default,,0,0,0,,reading what I've presented to
Dialogue: 0,0:20:35.15,0:20:35.39,Default,,0,0,0,,them.
Dialogue: 0,0:20:35.43,0:20:36.31,Default,,0,0,0,,Now I'd like, or the Dismiss
Dialogue: 0,0:20:36.31,0:20:39.03,Default,,0,0,0,,button style is a property on
Dialogue: 0,0:20:39.23,0:20:40.47,Default,,0,0,0,,SFSafariViewController.
Dialogue: 0,0:20:40.47,0:20:42.97,Default,,0,0,0,,As I mentioned it has these two
Dialogue: 0,0:20:42.97,0:20:43.70,Default,,0,0,0,,new options.
Dialogue: 0,0:20:44.11,0:20:45.59,Default,,0,0,0,,The default style will be Done
Dialogue: 0,0:20:45.90,0:20:46.95,Default,,0,0,0,,but you can choose which ever
Dialogue: 0,0:20:46.95,0:20:48.89,Default,,0,0,0,,style best fits your use case of
Dialogue: 0,0:20:48.89,0:20:50.01,Default,,0,0,0,,Safari View Controller.
Dialogue: 0,0:20:51.55,0:20:52.94,Default,,0,0,0,,The value can even be changed
Dialogue: 0,0:20:52.94,0:20:54.27,Default,,0,0,0,,while Safari View Controller is
Dialogue: 0,0:20:54.27,0:20:55.73,Default,,0,0,0,,presented, which Louie will
Dialogue: 0,0:20:55.73,0:20:56.67,Default,,0,0,0,,demonstrate later.
Dialogue: 0,0:20:56.67,0:21:00.67,Default,,0,0,0,,Now I'd like to talk to you
Dialogue: 0,0:21:00.67,0:21:02.14,Default,,0,0,0,,about a customization you can
Dialogue: 0,0:21:02.14,0:21:03.87,Default,,0,0,0,,make to the Share Sheet in
Dialogue: 0,0:21:03.87,0:21:04.98,Default,,0,0,0,,Safari View Controller.
Dialogue: 0,0:21:07.60,0:21:09.54,Default,,0,0,0,,Let's say I'm presenting a login
Dialogue: 0,0:21:09.57,0:21:10.43,Default,,0,0,0,,flow to the user.
Dialogue: 0,0:21:11.57,0:21:12.95,Default,,0,0,0,,When the tap the share button
Dialogue: 0,0:21:12.95,0:21:13.89,Default,,0,0,0,,they have all these different
Dialogue: 0,0:21:14.01,0:21:15.82,Default,,0,0,0,,actions that they can take, but
Dialogue: 0,0:21:15.82,0:21:16.84,Default,,0,0,0,,some of them don't really make
Dialogue: 0,0:21:16.84,0:21:17.81,Default,,0,0,0,,sense in this case.
Dialogue: 0,0:21:18.65,0:21:19.74,Default,,0,0,0,,They're probably not going to
Dialogue: 0,0:21:19.84,0:21:21.20,Default,,0,0,0,,send the page somewhere else
Dialogue: 0,0:21:21.52,0:21:22.63,Default,,0,0,0,,because it might disrupt the
Dialogue: 0,0:21:22.63,0:21:24.65,Default,,0,0,0,,login flow and the login might
Dialogue: 0,0:21:24.65,0:21:25.73,Default,,0,0,0,,now even work outside of the
Dialogue: 0,0:21:25.73,0:21:26.57,Default,,0,0,0,,context of my app.
Dialogue: 0,0:21:29.01,0:21:31.68,Default,,0,0,0,,Here, I've filtered out, so this
Dialogue: 0,0:21:31.68,0:21:33.79,Default,,0,0,0,,is what the actions that I don't
Dialogue: 0,0:21:33.79,0:21:34.28,Default,,0,0,0,,want to show.
Dialogue: 0,0:21:35.06,0:21:36.80,Default,,0,0,0,,On iOS 11 we're giving the
Dialogue: 0,0:21:36.80,0:21:38.57,Default,,0,0,0,,ability to filter out some of
Dialogue: 0,0:21:38.57,0:21:40.11,Default,,0,0,0,,these UIActivityTypes.
Dialogue: 0,0:21:41.27,0:21:43.90,Default,,0,0,0,,Here, I've filtered out AirDrop,
Dialogue: 0,0:21:44.07,0:21:46.46,Default,,0,0,0,,Mail, and Messages because my
Dialogue: 0,0:21:46.46,0:21:47.93,Default,,0,0,0,,users don't need them in this
Dialogue: 0,0:21:47.93,0:21:48.26,Default,,0,0,0,,case.
Dialogue: 0,0:21:50.35,0:21:52.35,Default,,0,0,0,,You make recognize this API on
Dialogue: 0,0:21:52.35,0:21:53.92,Default,,0,0,0,,UIActivityViewController.
Dialogue: 0,0:21:54.50,0:21:56.82,Default,,0,0,0,,It allows you to set an array of
Dialogue: 0,0:21:56.82,0:21:58.64,Default,,0,0,0,,UIActivityTypes that the user
Dialogue: 0,0:21:58.64,0:22:00.45,Default,,0,0,0,,doesn't need on your
Dialogue: 0,0:22:00.45,0:22:01.96,Default,,0,0,0,,UIActivityViewController.
Dialogue: 0,0:22:02.70,0:22:03.63,Default,,0,0,0,,We realize that if you're
Dialogue: 0,0:22:03.63,0:22:05.03,Default,,0,0,0,,implementing your own in-app web
Dialogue: 0,0:22:05.03,0:22:06.64,Default,,0,0,0,,browsing experience, you'd have
Dialogue: 0,0:22:06.64,0:22:08.06,Default,,0,0,0,,the ability to customize the
Dialogue: 0,0:22:08.06,0:22:09.27,Default,,0,0,0,,Share Sheet in this way.
Dialogue: 0,0:22:10.32,0:22:12.08,Default,,0,0,0,,So, in iOS 11 we're exposing
Dialogue: 0,0:22:12.08,0:22:13.55,Default,,0,0,0,,this same ability on
Dialogue: 0,0:22:13.73,0:22:16.58,Default,,0,0,0,,SFSafariViewControllerDelegate
Dialogue: 0,0:22:17.05,0:22:18.85,Default,,0,0,0,,as a method where you can return
Dialogue: 0,0:22:18.85,0:22:21.43,Default,,0,0,0,,an array of UIActivityTypes that
Dialogue: 0,0:22:21.43,0:22:22.85,Default,,0,0,0,,you don't want to be presented
Dialogue: 0,0:22:22.85,0:22:24.81,Default,,0,0,0,,to the user in the context of
Dialogue: 0,0:22:24.81,0:22:26.15,Default,,0,0,0,,your Safari View Controller.
Dialogue: 0,0:22:28.38,0:22:29.81,Default,,0,0,0,,Now, I'd like to talk about Bar
Dialogue: 0,0:22:29.81,0:22:31.37,Default,,0,0,0,,Collapsing in Safari View
Dialogue: 0,0:22:31.37,0:22:31.92,Default,,0,0,0,,Controller.
Dialogue: 0,0:22:33.50,0:22:36.76,Default,,0,0,0,,Safari View Controller's bars
Dialogue: 0,0:22:36.82,0:22:38.43,Default,,0,0,0,,collapse away while in browsing,
Dialogue: 0,0:22:38.89,0:22:39.91,Default,,0,0,0,,which lets me really get
Dialogue: 0,0:22:39.91,0:22:41.36,Default,,0,0,0,,immersed in my browsing
Dialogue: 0,0:22:41.36,0:22:42.09,Default,,0,0,0,,experience.
Dialogue: 0,0:22:43.55,0:22:45.69,Default,,0,0,0,,However, in some cases this bar
Dialogue: 0,0:22:45.69,0:22:46.91,Default,,0,0,0,,collapsing behavior can be
Dialogue: 0,0:22:46.91,0:22:47.59,Default,,0,0,0,,frustrating.
Dialogue: 0,0:22:48.28,0:22:49.84,Default,,0,0,0,,Let's say I have a login flow.
Dialogue: 0,0:22:50.49,0:22:52.32,Default,,0,0,0,,If bars are collapsed, the
Dialogue: 0,0:22:52.32,0:22:54.07,Default,,0,0,0,,Dismiss button gets hidden.
Dialogue: 0,0:22:54.31,0:22:55.68,Default,,0,0,0,,So, it's a bit more difficult to
Dialogue: 0,0:22:55.68,0:22:57.28,Default,,0,0,0,,Dismiss Safari View Controller.
Dialogue: 0,0:22:58.66,0:22:59.77,Default,,0,0,0,,So, in something quick like a
Dialogue: 0,0:22:59.77,0:23:02.81,Default,,0,0,0,,login flow, this standard bar
Dialogue: 0,0:23:02.81,0:23:04.66,Default,,0,0,0,,collapsing behavior might not
Dialogue: 0,0:23:04.66,0:23:06.64,Default,,0,0,0,,necessarily make sense.
Dialogue: 0,0:23:07.05,0:23:10.28,Default,,0,0,0,,On iOS 11, we're allowing you to
Dialogue: 0,0:23:10.28,0:23:11.48,Default,,0,0,0,,disable this standard bar
Dialogue: 0,0:23:11.48,0:23:12.98,Default,,0,0,0,,collapsing behavior if it best
Dialogue: 0,0:23:13.07,0:23:13.98,Default,,0,0,0,,fits your use case.
Dialogue: 0,0:23:15.44,0:23:17.37,Default,,0,0,0,,This will be a new property on
Dialogue: 0,0:23:17.37,0:23:18.75,Default,,0,0,0,,SFSafariViewController
Dialogue: 0,0:23:18.75,0:23:20.67,Default,,0,0,0,,.Configuration which will be
Dialogue: 0,0:23:20.67,0:23:22.20,Default,,0,0,0,,passed into Safari View
Dialogue: 0,0:23:22.20,0:23:23.66,Default,,0,0,0,,Controller's initializer.
Dialogue: 0,0:23:24.26,0:23:27.25,Default,,0,0,0,,It's best to leave this enabled
Dialogue: 0,0:23:27.60,0:23:29.47,Default,,0,0,0,,if your use case is show user's
Dialogue: 0,0:23:29.51,0:23:31.99,Default,,0,0,0,,browsing, or user's content that
Dialogue: 0,0:23:31.99,0:23:33.21,Default,,0,0,0,,they should really get immersed
Dialogue: 0,0:23:33.29,0:23:33.46,Default,,0,0,0,,in.
Dialogue: 0,0:23:34.24,0:23:35.69,Default,,0,0,0,,But, if it's important to always
Dialogue: 0,0:23:35.69,0:23:37.25,Default,,0,0,0,,have the Dismiss button shown,
Dialogue: 0,0:23:38.08,0:23:39.49,Default,,0,0,0,,you can disable this property.
Dialogue: 0,0:23:39.49,0:23:44.04,Default,,0,0,0,,Now, I'd like to welcome Louie
Dialogue: 0,0:23:44.04,0:23:45.48,Default,,0,0,0,,back to the stage to show you
Dialogue: 0,0:23:45.48,0:23:47.27,Default,,0,0,0,,how easy it is to use these new
Dialogue: 0,0:23:47.27,0:23:49.46,Default,,0,0,0,,APIs to tailor for his app's
Dialogue: 0,0:23:49.46,0:23:50.10,Default,,0,0,0,,experience.
Dialogue: 0,0:23:51.52,0:23:56.55,Default,,0,0,0,,[ Applause ]
Dialogue: 0,0:23:57.05,0:23:57.70,Default,,0,0,0,,>> Thanks, Chelsea.
Dialogue: 0,0:23:58.69,0:24:00.29,Default,,0,0,0,,I'm thrilled to show you how
Dialogue: 0,0:24:00.29,0:24:01.75,Default,,0,0,0,,easy it is to customize Safari
Dialogue: 0,0:24:01.75,0:24:03.29,Default,,0,0,0,,View Controller using these new
Dialogue: 0,0:24:03.29,0:24:05.22,Default,,0,0,0,,APIs and I'm going to give you a
Dialogue: 0,0:24:05.22,0:24:06.81,Default,,0,0,0,,sneak peak at the next app I'm
Dialogue: 0,0:24:06.81,0:24:07.42,Default,,0,0,0,,working on.
Dialogue: 0,0:24:09.06,0:24:11.08,Default,,0,0,0,,It's another pizza related app,
Dialogue: 0,0:24:11.27,0:24:12.94,Default,,0,0,0,,so I hope that's not too cheesy.
Dialogue: 0,0:24:13.46,0:24:16.83,Default,,0,0,0,,[laughter] This is a social app
Dialogue: 0,0:24:16.97,0:24:18.23,Default,,0,0,0,,called Pizza Stories.
Dialogue: 0,0:24:18.85,0:24:20.09,Default,,0,0,0,,It allows you to share all the
Dialogue: 0,0:24:20.09,0:24:21.60,Default,,0,0,0,,pizza related news in your life
Dialogue: 0,0:24:21.60,0:24:23.11,Default,,0,0,0,,in a visual format with your
Dialogue: 0,0:24:23.11,0:24:24.25,Default,,0,0,0,,friends and family.
Dialogue: 0,0:24:26.40,0:24:28.66,Default,,0,0,0,,By default, it when you're not
Dialogue: 0,0:24:28.66,0:24:30.28,Default,,0,0,0,,logged in, you get a list of
Dialogue: 0,0:24:30.28,0:24:31.63,Default,,0,0,0,,pizza brands that are sharing
Dialogue: 0,0:24:31.63,0:24:32.49,Default,,0,0,0,,some stories.
Dialogue: 0,0:24:33.64,0:24:34.96,Default,,0,0,0,,However, to get the best
Dialogue: 0,0:24:34.96,0:24:36.02,Default,,0,0,0,,experience out of this app,
Dialogue: 0,0:24:36.34,0:24:37.26,Default,,0,0,0,,you'll want to log-in.
Dialogue: 0,0:24:38.07,0:24:40.76,Default,,0,0,0,,I don't want users to have to
Dialogue: 0,0:24:40.76,0:24:42.88,Default,,0,0,0,,create and maintain a list of
Dialogue: 0,0:24:42.88,0:24:44.77,Default,,0,0,0,,their friends in my app, and I
Dialogue: 0,0:24:44.77,0:24:46.02,Default,,0,0,0,,don't own a social network that
Dialogue: 0,0:24:46.02,0:24:48.34,Default,,0,0,0,,already has this, so I want them
Dialogue: 0,0:24:48.34,0:24:49.74,Default,,0,0,0,,to be able to use an existing
Dialogue: 0,0:24:49.74,0:24:51.15,Default,,0,0,0,,list that they've already used
Dialogue: 0,0:24:51.43,0:24:53.37,Default,,0,0,0,,and created all of their friends
Dialogue: 0,0:24:54.05,0:24:55.77,Default,,0,0,0,,on an existing social network.
Dialogue: 0,0:24:56.63,0:24:58.20,Default,,0,0,0,,I'm using Safari View Controller
Dialogue: 0,0:24:58.34,0:24:59.44,Default,,0,0,0,,to let them log-in and
Dialogue: 0,0:24:59.44,0:25:00.79,Default,,0,0,0,,authenticate against this social
Dialogue: 0,0:25:00.79,0:25:01.18,Default,,0,0,0,,network.
Dialogue: 0,0:25:01.63,0:25:04.65,Default,,0,0,0,,I tap Log In, Safari View
Dialogue: 0,0:25:04.65,0:25:06.21,Default,,0,0,0,,Controller is shown and let's my
Dialogue: 0,0:25:06.21,0:25:08.29,Default,,0,0,0,,users log in with SampleChat a
Dialogue: 0,0:25:08.29,0:25:09.84,Default,,0,0,0,,really popular demo social
Dialogue: 0,0:25:09.84,0:25:10.27,Default,,0,0,0,,network.
Dialogue: 0,0:25:12.18,0:25:13.34,Default,,0,0,0,,You may have noticed that Safari
Dialogue: 0,0:25:13.34,0:25:15.12,Default,,0,0,0,,View Controller came in from
Dialogue: 0,0:25:15.12,0:25:16.23,Default,,0,0,0,,right to left like a
Dialogue: 0,0:25:16.23,0:25:18.07,Default,,0,0,0,,UINavigationController.
Dialogue: 0,0:25:18.70,0:25:19.90,Default,,0,0,0,,My app doesn't use this
Dialogue: 0,0:25:19.90,0:25:21.74,Default,,0,0,0,,paradigm, so that feels a little
Dialogue: 0,0:25:21.74,0:25:22.16,Default,,0,0,0,,weird.
Dialogue: 0,0:25:23.01,0:25:25.71,Default,,0,0,0,,I have already made it so that
Dialogue: 0,0:25:25.71,0:25:27.08,Default,,0,0,0,,Safari View Controller takes on
Dialogue: 0,0:25:27.08,0:25:30.60,Default,,0,0,0,,the colors of my app, but the
Dialogue: 0,0:25:30.60,0:25:32.16,Default,,0,0,0,,transition didn't feel right for
Dialogue: 0,0:25:32.16,0:25:33.11,Default,,0,0,0,,my app.
Dialogue: 0,0:25:33.25,0:25:35.95,Default,,0,0,0,,Similarly, saying Done doesn't
Dialogue: 0,0:25:35.95,0:25:36.90,Default,,0,0,0,,really make sense here.
Dialogue: 0,0:25:37.32,0:25:38.45,Default,,0,0,0,,I want to communicate to my
Dialogue: 0,0:25:38.45,0:25:40.51,Default,,0,0,0,,users that tapping this button
Dialogue: 0,0:25:40.51,0:25:42.25,Default,,0,0,0,,will cancel this login session.
Dialogue: 0,0:25:42.76,0:25:44.60,Default,,0,0,0,,So, it's clear what's going to
Dialogue: 0,0:25:44.69,0:25:45.62,Default,,0,0,0,,happen when they tap it.
Dialogue: 0,0:25:46.27,0:25:48.06,Default,,0,0,0,,And if my users are reading the
Dialogue: 0,0:25:48.06,0:25:49.49,Default,,0,0,0,,Terms of Service and they scroll
Dialogue: 0,0:25:49.49,0:25:51.25,Default,,0,0,0,,down a little bit, the bars
Dialogue: 0,0:25:51.25,0:25:51.86,Default,,0,0,0,,collapse.
Dialogue: 0,0:25:52.19,0:25:53.86,Default,,0,0,0,,This might nice in some other
Dialogue: 0,0:25:53.86,0:25:55.55,Default,,0,0,0,,web pages, but here it could
Dialogue: 0,0:25:55.55,0:25:56.37,Default,,0,0,0,,just get annoying.
Dialogue: 0,0:25:56.79,0:25:58.70,Default,,0,0,0,,If they want to cancel, it's two
Dialogue: 0,0:25:58.70,0:26:00.00,Default,,0,0,0,,taps away instead of one.
Dialogue: 0,0:26:01.28,0:26:02.63,Default,,0,0,0,,So, I'll show you how to improve
Dialogue: 0,0:26:02.63,0:26:04.18,Default,,0,0,0,,Safari View Controller to fit
Dialogue: 0,0:26:04.18,0:26:08.37,Default,,0,0,0,,this log in a little bit better.
Dialogue: 0,0:26:08.57,0:26:09.38,Default,,0,0,0,,Here's where I'm presenting
Dialogue: 0,0:26:09.38,0:26:10.47,Default,,0,0,0,,Safari View Controller.
Dialogue: 0,0:26:11.02,0:26:12.34,Default,,0,0,0,,Like before, it's pretty simple.
Dialogue: 0,0:26:12.86,0:26:15.13,Default,,0,0,0,,I'm creating a URL and then
Dialogue: 0,0:26:15.42,0:26:16.55,Default,,0,0,0,,passing that to Safari View
Dialogue: 0,0:26:16.55,0:26:17.64,Default,,0,0,0,,Controller's initializer.
Dialogue: 0,0:26:18.95,0:26:20.33,Default,,0,0,0,,Customizing the colors as I
Dialogue: 0,0:26:20.33,0:26:21.13,Default,,0,0,0,,showed you before.
Dialogue: 0,0:26:21.71,0:26:23.92,Default,,0,0,0,,And then presenting Safari View
Dialogue: 0,0:26:23.92,0:26:24.37,Default,,0,0,0,,Controller.
Dialogue: 0,0:26:25.20,0:26:27.15,Default,,0,0,0,,But let's make some changes.
Dialogue: 0,0:26:27.31,0:26:28.53,Default,,0,0,0,,First, let's make sure that the
Dialogue: 0,0:26:28.53,0:26:29.73,Default,,0,0,0,,bars don't collapse when they
Dialogue: 0,0:26:29.73,0:26:30.31,Default,,0,0,0,,scroll down.
Dialogue: 0,0:26:34.96,0:26:36.21,Default,,0,0,0,,So, what I've done here is
Dialogue: 0,0:26:36.21,0:26:37.67,Default,,0,0,0,,created a Safari View Controller
Dialogue: 0,0:26:37.67,0:26:39.83,Default,,0,0,0,,configuration object and then
Dialogue: 0,0:26:39.83,0:26:41.42,Default,,0,0,0,,set its barCollapsingEnabled
Dialogue: 0,0:26:41.42,0:26:42.54,Default,,0,0,0,,property to false.
Dialogue: 0,0:26:42.87,0:26:44.14,Default,,0,0,0,,This way when they scroll down
Dialogue: 0,0:26:44.14,0:26:45.27,Default,,0,0,0,,the bars won't collapse, they'll
Dialogue: 0,0:26:45.27,0:26:46.56,Default,,0,0,0,,still stay full height.
Dialogue: 0,0:26:47.57,0:26:49.12,Default,,0,0,0,,I then pass this in to Safari
Dialogue: 0,0:26:49.12,0:26:50.31,Default,,0,0,0,,View Controller's initializer.
Dialogue: 0,0:26:51.80,0:26:52.59,Default,,0,0,0,,Let's make a couple other
Dialogue: 0,0:26:52.59,0:26:53.30,Default,,0,0,0,,changes.
Dialogue: 0,0:26:55.02,0:26:57.06,Default,,0,0,0,,I've done two different things
Dialogue: 0,0:26:57.06,0:26:57.31,Default,,0,0,0,,here.
Dialogue: 0,0:26:57.57,0:26:58.79,Default,,0,0,0,,The first, is setting
Dialogue: 0,0:26:58.79,0:27:01.21,Default,,0,0,0,,dismissButtonStyle to Cancel so
Dialogue: 0,0:27:01.21,0:27:02.63,Default,,0,0,0,,that the button will say Cancel
Dialogue: 0,0:27:02.63,0:27:03.73,Default,,0,0,0,,instead of Done, which is the
Dialogue: 0,0:27:03.73,0:27:04.22,Default,,0,0,0,,default.
Dialogue: 0,0:27:05.54,0:27:06.65,Default,,0,0,0,,Second change I've made is
Dialogue: 0,0:27:06.65,0:27:07.90,Default,,0,0,0,,slightly more complicated.
Dialogue: 0,0:27:08.35,0:27:09.27,Default,,0,0,0,,I'm overriding the
Dialogue: 0,0:27:09.27,0:27:10.67,Default,,0,0,0,,transitioningDelegate of Safari
Dialogue: 0,0:27:10.67,0:27:12.20,Default,,0,0,0,,View Controller to myself.
Dialogue: 0,0:27:13.15,0:27:14.49,Default,,0,0,0,,Since I haven't implemented any
Dialogue: 0,0:27:14.49,0:27:15.27,Default,,0,0,0,,of the methods of
Dialogue: 0,0:27:15.27,0:27:16.58,Default,,0,0,0,,UITransitioningDelegate, I'm
Dialogue: 0,0:27:16.58,0:27:18.20,Default,,0,0,0,,just going to get the standard
Dialogue: 0,0:27:18.20,0:27:20.35,Default,,0,0,0,,system default behavior where a
Dialogue: 0,0:27:20.35,0:27:21.61,Default,,0,0,0,,view comes in from bottom to
Dialogue: 0,0:27:21.61,0:27:22.04,Default,,0,0,0,,top.
Dialogue: 0,0:27:23.48,0:27:24.46,Default,,0,0,0,,I'll rebuild and show you how
Dialogue: 0,0:27:24.46,0:27:25.82,Default,,0,0,0,,this works in Pizza Stories.
Dialogue: 0,0:27:29.50,0:27:32.29,Default,,0,0,0,,Now when I tap Log In, Safari
Dialogue: 0,0:27:32.29,0:27:33.44,Default,,0,0,0,,View Controller came in from
Dialogue: 0,0:27:33.44,0:27:34.26,Default,,0,0,0,,bottom to top.
Dialogue: 0,0:27:35.14,0:27:36.43,Default,,0,0,0,,Now you may notice here, the
Dialogue: 0,0:27:36.43,0:27:37.22,Default,,0,0,0,,view is blank.
Dialogue: 0,0:27:37.40,0:27:38.73,Default,,0,0,0,,This is a bug on Seed 1.
Dialogue: 0,0:27:38.79,0:27:40.14,Default,,0,0,0,,If you do run into this, I'll
Dialogue: 0,0:27:40.14,0:27:41.03,Default,,0,0,0,,show you how to fix it.
Dialogue: 0,0:27:41.51,0:27:42.30,Default,,0,0,0,,You can either pull down
Dialogue: 0,0:27:42.30,0:27:44.21,Default,,0,0,0,,Notification Center or press the
Dialogue: 0,0:27:44.21,0:27:46.51,Default,,0,0,0,,Home button and then go back in
Dialogue: 0,0:27:46.59,0:27:49.64,Default,,0,0,0,,and the page loads.
Dialogue: 0,0:27:49.64,0:27:51.75,Default,,0,0,0,,So, in addition to the new
Dialogue: 0,0:27:51.75,0:27:54.12,Default,,0,0,0,,presentation, the Dismiss button
Dialogue: 0,0:27:54.12,0:27:55.63,Default,,0,0,0,,says Cancel to better indicate
Dialogue: 0,0:27:55.63,0:27:56.95,Default,,0,0,0,,to my users what tapping this
Dialogue: 0,0:27:56.95,0:27:57.33,Default,,0,0,0,,will do.
Dialogue: 0,0:27:57.89,0:28:00.51,Default,,0,0,0,,And when I scroll down, the bars
Dialogue: 0,0:28:00.51,0:28:01.19,Default,,0,0,0,,don't squish.
Dialogue: 0,0:28:02.37,0:28:03.38,Default,,0,0,0,,So, we're almost there.
Dialogue: 0,0:28:03.86,0:28:04.95,Default,,0,0,0,,However, there's one more change
Dialogue: 0,0:28:04.95,0:28:05.42,Default,,0,0,0,,I want to make.
Dialogue: 0,0:28:07.12,0:28:08.31,Default,,0,0,0,,Right now, it makes sense for
Dialogue: 0,0:28:08.31,0:28:09.47,Default,,0,0,0,,the button to say Cancel.
Dialogue: 0,0:28:10.48,0:28:11.82,Default,,0,0,0,,But, when my users successfully
Dialogue: 0,0:28:11.82,0:28:13.39,Default,,0,0,0,,logged in, it shouldn't say
Dialogue: 0,0:28:13.39,0:28:13.92,Default,,0,0,0,,Cancel.
Dialogue: 0,0:28:13.92,0:28:15.11,Default,,0,0,0,,I want to indicate to them that
Dialogue: 0,0:28:15.11,0:28:16.59,Default,,0,0,0,,it's okay to dismiss after that.
Dialogue: 0,0:28:18.30,0:28:19.62,Default,,0,0,0,,So, as Chelsea mentioned before,
Dialogue: 0,0:28:19.62,0:28:20.56,Default,,0,0,0,,what's really cool about this
Dialogue: 0,0:28:20.56,0:28:21.98,Default,,0,0,0,,property is it can be changed
Dialogue: 0,0:28:21.98,0:28:23.26,Default,,0,0,0,,even after I've already
Dialogue: 0,0:28:23.37,0:28:24.30,Default,,0,0,0,,presented Safari View
Dialogue: 0,0:28:24.30,0:28:24.82,Default,,0,0,0,,Controller.
Dialogue: 0,0:28:26.31,0:28:27.85,Default,,0,0,0,,When my user logs in with
Dialogue: 0,0:28:27.85,0:28:29.87,Default,,0,0,0,,SampleChat, they redirect to a
Dialogue: 0,0:28:29.87,0:28:31.55,Default,,0,0,0,,URL scheme that my app handles.
Dialogue: 0,0:28:32.09,0:28:34.65,Default,,0,0,0,,That gets handled in my
Dialogue: 0,0:28:34.65,0:28:36.31,Default,,0,0,0,,AppDelegate in this method.
Dialogue: 0,0:28:37.02,0:28:38.00,Default,,0,0,0,,And what I'm doing here is I'm
Dialogue: 0,0:28:38.00,0:28:39.22,Default,,0,0,0,,making sure that there's a log
Dialogue: 0,0:28:39.22,0:28:40.88,Default,,0,0,0,,in token to indicate that the
Dialogue: 0,0:28:40.88,0:28:42.80,Default,,0,0,0,,user's authenticated, then I'm
Dialogue: 0,0:28:42.80,0:28:44.11,Default,,0,0,0,,sending a message to elsewhere
Dialogue: 0,0:28:44.11,0:28:47.25,Default,,0,0,0,,in my app giving it that token.
Dialogue: 0,0:28:48.29,0:28:49.37,Default,,0,0,0,,I'm handling that here.
Dialogue: 0,0:28:50.29,0:28:51.55,Default,,0,0,0,,And I'm doing that because I
Dialogue: 0,0:28:51.55,0:28:52.56,Default,,0,0,0,,like to keep this code
Dialogue: 0,0:28:52.56,0:28:53.23,Default,,0,0,0,,organized.
Dialogue: 0,0:28:53.23,0:28:54.38,Default,,0,0,0,,I want everything related to
Dialogue: 0,0:28:54.38,0:28:56.26,Default,,0,0,0,,Login in one place rather than
Dialogue: 0,0:28:56.26,0:28:57.21,Default,,0,0,0,,having it in a few different
Dialogue: 0,0:28:57.21,0:28:57.84,Default,,0,0,0,,places.
Dialogue: 0,0:28:59.20,0:29:00.18,Default,,0,0,0,,Now that I know that the user
Dialogue: 0,0:29:00.18,0:29:02.11,Default,,0,0,0,,has successfully logged in, I
Dialogue: 0,0:29:02.94,0:29:04.13,Default,,0,0,0,,can change the
Dialogue: 0,0:29:04.13,0:29:05.80,Default,,0,0,0,,dismissButtonStyle of Safari
Dialogue: 0,0:29:05.80,0:29:07.91,Default,,0,0,0,,View Controller to Done instead
Dialogue: 0,0:29:07.91,0:29:08.54,Default,,0,0,0,,of Cancel.
Dialogue: 0,0:29:10.36,0:29:11.23,Default,,0,0,0,,So, I'll rebuild and I'll show
Dialogue: 0,0:29:11.23,0:29:12.62,Default,,0,0,0,,you how this all comes together
Dialogue: 0,0:29:12.62,0:29:13.53,Default,,0,0,0,,in Pizza Stories.
Dialogue: 0,0:29:24.08,0:29:26.57,Default,,0,0,0,,Now, when I tap Log In, Safari
Dialogue: 0,0:29:26.57,0:29:27.25,Default,,0,0,0,,View Controller is still
Dialogue: 0,0:29:27.25,0:29:28.67,Default,,0,0,0,,presented from bottom to top and
Dialogue: 0,0:29:28.67,0:29:29.75,Default,,0,0,0,,the button initially does say
Dialogue: 0,0:29:29.75,0:29:30.22,Default,,0,0,0,,Cancel.
Dialogue: 0,0:29:31.51,0:29:32.90,Default,,0,0,0,,With just a couple taps I can
Dialogue: 0,0:29:32.90,0:29:35.90,Default,,0,0,0,,use AutoFill to log in.
Dialogue: 0,0:29:36.12,0:29:37.72,Default,,0,0,0,,Now, SampleChat is asking the
Dialogue: 0,0:29:37.72,0:29:39.86,Default,,0,0,0,,user if they want to allow this
Dialogue: 0,0:29:39.86,0:29:41.83,Default,,0,0,0,,app, in this case Pizza Stories,
Dialogue: 0,0:29:42.02,0:29:43.63,Default,,0,0,0,,to use their account for their
Dialogue: 0,0:29:43.63,0:29:45.48,Default,,0,0,0,,friends list and their email.
Dialogue: 0,0:29:45.48,0:29:46.96,Default,,0,0,0,,I'll allow that.
Dialogue: 0,0:29:48.00,0:29:49.47,Default,,0,0,0,,And now that I'm logged in, the
Dialogue: 0,0:29:49.47,0:29:51.61,Default,,0,0,0,,Done button, the Dismiss button
Dialogue: 0,0:29:51.61,0:29:53.06,Default,,0,0,0,,has changed to say Done to
Dialogue: 0,0:29:53.06,0:29:54.64,Default,,0,0,0,,better indicate to my users it's
Dialogue: 0,0:29:54.64,0:29:56.43,Default,,0,0,0,,okay to dismiss now.
Dialogue: 0,0:29:57.52,0:30:00.69,Default,,0,0,0,,[ Applause ]
Dialogue: 0,0:30:01.19,0:30:04.05,Default,,0,0,0,,Thanks. So, when I dismiss, now
Dialogue: 0,0:30:04.05,0:30:05.35,Default,,0,0,0,,I get all of my friends showing
Dialogue: 0,0:30:05.35,0:30:07.00,Default,,0,0,0,,up in my, and I can see all
Dialogue: 0,0:30:07.00,0:30:07.84,Default,,0,0,0,,their stories.
Dialogue: 0,0:30:08.59,0:30:09.60,Default,,0,0,0,,This might make me crave some
Dialogue: 0,0:30:09.60,0:30:10.50,Default,,0,0,0,,pizza later on though.
Dialogue: 0,0:30:11.44,0:30:14.77,Default,,0,0,0,,Thanks, and this is how easy it
Dialogue: 0,0:30:14.77,0:30:16.11,Default,,0,0,0,,is to customize Safari View
Dialogue: 0,0:30:16.11,0:30:17.95,Default,,0,0,0,,Controller using the new APIs in
Dialogue: 0,0:30:18.05,0:30:20.35,Default,,0,0,0,,iOS 11 to tailor it to your app
Dialogue: 0,0:30:20.61,0:30:21.55,Default,,0,0,0,,and make a great log in
Dialogue: 0,0:30:21.55,0:30:22.27,Default,,0,0,0,,experience.
Dialogue: 0,0:30:22.77,0:30:23.88,Default,,0,0,0,,Thank you so much and I'll hand
Dialogue: 0,0:30:23.88,0:30:24.66,Default,,0,0,0,,it back over to Chelsea.
Dialogue: 0,0:30:26.52,0:30:30.27,Default,,0,0,0,,[ Applause ]
Dialogue: 0,0:30:30.77,0:30:31.75,Default,,0,0,0,,>> Thanks, Louie.
Dialogue: 0,0:30:32.12,0:30:33.57,Default,,0,0,0,,I think Louie is going to making
Dialogue: 0,0:30:33.57,0:30:35.03,Default,,0,0,0,,a lot of dough off that one.
Dialogue: 0,0:30:37.56,0:30:38.71,Default,,0,0,0,,[laughter] Louie just showed you
Dialogue: 0,0:30:38.82,0:30:40.75,Default,,0,0,0,,how with a few key improvements,
Dialogue: 0,0:30:41.10,0:30:42.73,Default,,0,0,0,,he made, he took his log in flow
Dialogue: 0,0:30:42.73,0:30:43.95,Default,,0,0,0,,with Safari View Controller to
Dialogue: 0,0:30:43.95,0:30:44.79,Default,,0,0,0,,the next level.
Dialogue: 0,0:30:45.64,0:30:47.74,Default,,0,0,0,,He did this by using a custom
Dialogue: 0,0:30:47.74,0:30:50.01,Default,,0,0,0,,presentation style that it felt
Dialogue: 0,0:30:50.01,0:30:51.71,Default,,0,0,0,,more like the presentation style
Dialogue: 0,0:30:51.71,0:30:52.16,Default,,0,0,0,,in his app.
Dialogue: 0,0:30:53.74,0:30:55.29,Default,,0,0,0,,He changed the Dismiss button to
Dialogue: 0,0:30:55.29,0:30:57.26,Default,,0,0,0,,say Cancel so that users know
Dialogue: 0,0:30:57.64,0:30:59.10,Default,,0,0,0,,that if they tap that button
Dialogue: 0,0:30:59.10,0:31:00.57,Default,,0,0,0,,they'll be cancelling log in
Dialogue: 0,0:31:00.57,0:31:01.85,Default,,0,0,0,,with the third-party service
Dialogue: 0,0:31:01.85,0:31:04.00,Default,,0,0,0,,he's asking them to log in with.
Dialogue: 0,0:31:05.43,0:31:07.07,Default,,0,0,0,,He turned off bar collapsing.
Dialogue: 0,0:31:07.24,0:31:08.65,Default,,0,0,0,,This way if the user reads the
Dialogue: 0,0:31:08.65,0:31:10.46,Default,,0,0,0,,Terms of Service and decides
Dialogue: 0,0:31:10.46,0:31:11.62,Default,,0,0,0,,that they don't want to use that
Dialogue: 0,0:31:11.62,0:31:13.11,Default,,0,0,0,,service, they can quickly tap
Dialogue: 0,0:31:13.11,0:31:14.72,Default,,0,0,0,,cancel to exit Safari View
Dialogue: 0,0:31:14.72,0:31:15.32,Default,,0,0,0,,Controller.
Dialogue: 0,0:31:15.89,0:31:19.52,Default,,0,0,0,,And he changed the button to say
Dialogue: 0,0:31:19.52,0:31:21.38,Default,,0,0,0,,Done once the user had allowed
Dialogue: 0,0:31:21.38,0:31:22.72,Default,,0,0,0,,access to that third-party
Dialogue: 0,0:31:22.72,0:31:23.11,Default,,0,0,0,,service.
Dialogue: 0,0:31:23.70,0:31:25.18,Default,,0,0,0,,This way they know that they've
Dialogue: 0,0:31:25.24,0:31:26.36,Default,,0,0,0,,finished logging in.
Dialogue: 0,0:31:26.87,0:31:30.73,Default,,0,0,0,,One of the main things that we
Dialogue: 0,0:31:30.73,0:31:31.93,Default,,0,0,0,,want you to get out of this
Dialogue: 0,0:31:31.99,0:31:34.32,Default,,0,0,0,,presentation is that we hear
Dialogue: 0,0:31:34.32,0:31:34.62,Default,,0,0,0,,you.
Dialogue: 0,0:31:35.77,0:31:37.18,Default,,0,0,0,,The new APIs that we've talked
Dialogue: 0,0:31:37.18,0:31:39.36,Default,,0,0,0,,about today were inspired by
Dialogue: 0,0:31:39.49,0:31:40.50,Default,,0,0,0,,feedback from you.
Dialogue: 0,0:31:41.48,0:31:43.10,Default,,0,0,0,,We really encourage you to keep
Dialogue: 0,0:31:43.10,0:31:45.02,Default,,0,0,0,,giving us feature requests and
Dialogue: 0,0:31:45.02,0:31:46.23,Default,,0,0,0,,filing bug reports.
Dialogue: 0,0:31:47.05,0:31:48.51,Default,,0,0,0,,And also letting us know if
Dialogue: 0,0:31:48.55,0:31:49.27,Default,,0,0,0,,there are any other
Dialogue: 0,0:31:49.27,0:31:51.03,Default,,0,0,0,,customizations you'd like to see
Dialogue: 0,0:31:51.14,0:31:52.42,Default,,0,0,0,,in Safari View Controller.
Dialogue: 0,0:31:53.50,0:31:54.64,Default,,0,0,0,,So, keep talking to us.
Dialogue: 0,0:31:57.03,0:32:00.92,Default,,0,0,0,,In summary, Safari View
Dialogue: 0,0:32:00.92,0:32:03.79,Default,,0,0,0,,Controller gives you an easy
Dialogue: 0,0:32:03.79,0:32:05.57,Default,,0,0,0,,in-app web browsing experience.
Dialogue: 0,0:32:05.90,0:32:07.03,Default,,0,0,0,,With just a couple lines of
Dialogue: 0,0:32:07.03,0:32:08.99,Default,,0,0,0,,code, you can get Safari View
Dialogue: 0,0:32:08.99,0:32:10.72,Default,,0,0,0,,Controller up and running in
Dialogue: 0,0:32:10.72,0:32:11.39,Default,,0,0,0,,your app.
Dialogue: 0,0:32:12.88,0:32:14.21,Default,,0,0,0,,Safari View Controller is
Dialogue: 0,0:32:14.35,0:32:15.82,Default,,0,0,0,,perfect for authenticating with
Dialogue: 0,0:32:15.82,0:32:17.97,Default,,0,0,0,,third-party services because it
Dialogue: 0,0:32:17.97,0:32:19.64,Default,,0,0,0,,provides a security that users
Dialogue: 0,0:32:19.64,0:32:21.40,Default,,0,0,0,,need and the features that they
Dialogue: 0,0:32:21.40,0:32:24.69,Default,,0,0,0,,love while getting logged in.
Dialogue: 0,0:32:26.18,0:32:27.88,Default,,0,0,0,,There are many improvements to
Dialogue: 0,0:32:27.88,0:32:29.48,Default,,0,0,0,,Safari View Controller on iOS
Dialogue: 0,0:32:29.48,0:32:30.06,Default,,0,0,0,,11.
Dialogue: 0,0:32:30.54,0:32:31.81,Default,,0,0,0,,Safari View Controller's new
Dialogue: 0,0:32:31.81,0:32:33.69,Default,,0,0,0,,look and the new APIs that we've
Dialogue: 0,0:32:33.69,0:32:35.81,Default,,0,0,0,,introduced can help Safari View
Dialogue: 0,0:32:35.81,0:32:37.62,Default,,0,0,0,,Controller feel at home in your
Dialogue: 0,0:32:37.99,0:32:38.06,Default,,0,0,0,,app.
Dialogue: 0,0:32:40.27,0:32:41.93,Default,,0,0,0,,If you've taken a look at Safari
Dialogue: 0,0:32:41.93,0:32:43.81,Default,,0,0,0,,View Controller in the past but
Dialogue: 0,0:32:43.81,0:32:45.22,Default,,0,0,0,,maybe it didn't quite fit your
Dialogue: 0,0:32:45.22,0:32:46.94,Default,,0,0,0,,use case, we encourage you to
Dialogue: 0,0:32:46.94,0:32:47.81,Default,,0,0,0,,take another look.
Dialogue: 0,0:32:48.90,0:32:50.67,Default,,0,0,0,,These improvements on iOS 11 and
Dialogue: 0,0:32:50.91,0:32:52.55,Default,,0,0,0,,the APIs that have been added
Dialogue: 0,0:32:52.76,0:32:53.79,Default,,0,0,0,,were inspired by you.
Dialogue: 0,0:32:54.66,0:32:55.67,Default,,0,0,0,,So, we really hope there's
Dialogue: 0,0:32:55.67,0:32:57.76,Default,,0,0,0,,something in there for you.
Dialogue: 0,0:32:58.88,0:33:00.58,Default,,0,0,0,,For more information on this
Dialogue: 0,0:33:00.58,0:33:02.26,Default,,0,0,0,,session you can view the page
Dialogue: 0,0:33:02.30,0:33:02.86,Default,,0,0,0,,listed here.
Dialogue: 0,0:33:02.86,0:33:06.86,Default,,0,0,0,,I'd like to tell you about some
Dialogue: 0,0:33:06.86,0:33:08.15,Default,,0,0,0,,related sessions that you might
Dialogue: 0,0:33:08.15,0:33:09.10,Default,,0,0,0,,be interested in.
Dialogue: 0,0:33:09.70,0:33:11.36,Default,,0,0,0,,These are all available on the
Dialogue: 0,0:33:11.36,0:33:12.94,Default,,0,0,0,,WWDC website and app.
Dialogue: 0,0:33:14.12,0:33:15.29,Default,,0,0,0,,We've talked a lot about getting
Dialogue: 0,0:33:15.29,0:33:16.64,Default,,0,0,0,,your user authenticated with a
Dialogue: 0,0:33:16.71,0:33:18.29,Default,,0,0,0,,third-party service using Safari
